name: ALMOND MILK
description: Almond Milk is an inviting, soft white color with a hint of warmth and part of our High Hide Whites Collection. With its creamy undertones and just a hint of yellow, Almond Milk adds depth and dimension to any space. As an excellent multipurpose white, Almond Milk works with a range of design styles including Traditional farmhouse and Modern loft aesthetics. This soft white color is a popular choice for walls, ceiling, trim and cabinetry and is a perfect all-over color for an open space plan.

name: WHITE DAISY
description: White Daisy is a refreshing white color with just a subtle hint of warmth and part of our High Hide Whites Collection. Delivering style and sophistication, White Daisy plays well with other colors, yet can stand on its own. Add White Daisy to a modern space for a clean look or to a traditional beachside cottage to balance out blue and green color schemes. Does your room face east or north? These rooms don’t get as much warm, natural light so to counterbalance these cooler, shady rooms, try White Daisy.

name: COCONUT GROVE
description: Coconut Grove is a clean white color with just a subtle hint of warmth and part of our High Hide Whites Collection. As a classic go-to white that appears clean and neutral in most lighting situations, Coconut Grove is an ideal color choice for dark wood accents and other natural materials. This elegant white color is also an excellent choice to pair with pastel color schemes.

name: SWISS MERINGUE
description: Swiss Meringue is a neutral, soft white color that balances warmth and coolness and is part of our High Hide Whites Collection. This alabaster shade of white is a versatile hue that can effortlessly pair with industrial design elements like metal or rustic elements like distressed woods. With its neutrality and very little undertones, Swiss Meringue is a perfect color choice for an all-white aesthetic or as a complement to jewel tones.

name: AT FIRST LIGHT
description: At First Light is a neutral white color with depth and part of our High Hide Whites Collection. As a neutral color, At First Light is a white color that can work with any design style and is perfect for both traditional and contemporary design projects. The softness of this neutral white color make it an ideal choice to design spaces that feels open and airy without feeling cold and complements spaces that get a lot of natural lighting.

name: NORTH TO ALASKA
description: North to Alaska is a cool, crisp and clean white color with a touch of gray and part of our High Hide Whites Collection. Reminding one of a snowy morning, this bright white color is versatile and will work for any design aesthetic. North to Alaska is a fresh, clean and modern white color, which makes it an excellent choice for trim and cabinetry, as well as modern and contemporary open spaces. This white color also pairs well with cool colors such as grays and blues.

name: SUGAR SWIZZLE
description: Sugar Swizzle color is a clean, cooler white with a subtle touch of gray undertones, offering both versatility and charm. This classic white has depth, making it a refreshing choice for modern spaces, particularly in open floor plans. Its light, airy quality is perfect for creating serene, minimalist atmospheres, while its muted sophistication makes it an excellent neutral backdrop. Whether used on its own or paired with other whites or cool grays, Sugar Swizzle lends elegance and dimension to any room without feeling too stark or cold.

name: CLASSIC WHITE
description: Classic White is a cooler, neutral white color and is part of our High Hide Whites Collection. Inspired by classic elegance and clean architecture, Classic White is a snowy white color and the ideal neutral shade for bright and airy spaces and is a perfect blank canvas for art-filled spaces. This cool white color is illuminating and pure, making it an ideal white color for whole home design or for use on trim, ceilings and cabinetry.

name: BE COOL
description: Be Cool is a cool, crisp white color and is part of our High Hide Whites Collection. Brilliant and sparkling with energy, Be Cool is an ideal white color for use on trim work and cabinetry. The more neutral, reflective quality of this cool white makes it a perfect choice for contemporary and modern architecture. This clean white pairs beautifully with grays and other cool color shades. Is your room south-facing? Cool white colors such as Be Cool are ideal choices to counterbalance the natural warming tones from southern exposure.

name: ICY WHITE
description: Icy White is a cool, snowy clean white color and is part of our High Hide Whites Collection. This cool, brilliant white conjures up images of winter wonderlands and provides a welcome ambiance to modern spaces. This versatile white color provides the perfect backdrop to artwork and brightens a room with limited natural lighting.

name: COY
description: Coy is a pastel-tinted white color with pink undertones and part of our Whites Collection. With its soft, subtle tint of color, Coy is a delicate, pastel white color that is versatile enough to use as a wall color or cabinetry. With the continuing trend of pink hues everywhere, Coy is an ideal choice to bring in just a hint of color for modern design styles, as well and traditional historic architecture such as Victorian and Craftsman.

name: STRAWBERRY DUST
description: Strawberry Dust is a precious, warm white paint color with pink undertones. This sweet tart pink has a barely there quality, with an energetic and playful energy that is just waiting for its moment to shine.

name: AJO LILY
description: Ajo Lily is a tinted warm white with a touch of yellow color and part of the Whites Collection. Also called desert lily, this warm white is perfect for a desert modern or Bohemian design styled home paired with layers of muted warm, rosy neutrals, sage greens and misted violets to complete a well-rounded color palette.

name: ALABASTER
description: Alabaster is a soft, off-white color with a hint of beige undertones and part of the Whites Collection. A simple neutral hue with a touch of warmth allows Alabaster to be the perfect backdrop color to highlight any design aesthetic. Try Alabaster on kitchen cabinetry or pair with décor and other warmer paint colors for a flawless finish.

name: FRENCH WHITE
description: Ooh la la! This barely blushing, warm white paint color has a subtle touch of rose. French White is a cozy, elegant, and traditional color.

name: COTTAGE WHITE
description: Cottage White color is a soft warm white with a touch of yellow and part of the Whites Collection. With its soft, warm undertones, Cottage White looks lovely in bedrooms where it adds a warm glow to the welcoming retreat.

name: MAGNOLIA
description: Magnolia is an ivory off-white and part of our Whites collection. This soft white is a reminder of that the first hints of spring are the many trees and flowers that begin to bloom. Try Magnolia as a warmer white option throughout your home interior.

name: VANILLA SHAKE
description: Vanilla Shake is a natural, milky white color with a touch of warmth and part of our Whites Collection. With its mildly warm undertones, this color creates an inviting and elegant scene. Inherently versatile and tranquil, paint Vanilla Shake throughout the home for a sense of calm.

name: BIRCH WHITE
description: Birch White color is an off-white and is part of our Whites Collection. Inspired by the birch trees that look so beautiful in the fall with the white bark and yellow leaves. If you’re looking for a creamier, warm white, try Birch White.

name: PEARL WHITE
description: Pearl White color is a creamy warm white and part of our Whites Collection. Inspired by the white color of precious pearls, Pearl White paint creates an understated, calming backdrop on a home's interior walls. A great choice for a traditional or beach home as a base color. Pair with cool blues and grays to balance out the warmth.

name: WHITE SAND
description: White Sand is an off-white color and part of the Whites Collection. As a warm, understated color, White Sand appeals to both traditional and modern design styles. Create a neutral backdrop to traditional design spaces using this off white color or pair with a deep color for a high-contrast look.

name: GARDENIA
description: Gardenia color is a bright, warm white and part of our Whites collection. Pair Gardenia with warm woods and pattern to create a cozy retreat.

name: WHITE HEAT
description: White Heat is a beachy, bright warm white color and part of our Whites Collection. With the touch of warmth highlighted in this color, White Heat is perfect, classic choice for brighter spaces with lots of natural light and is an effortless choice for Spanish and Mediterranean architectural styles.

name: BONE CHINA
description: Bone China is a warm off white and part of the Whites Collection. Understated and elegant, Bone China is extremely versatile and neither too warm nor cool. Try Bone China as a whole home neutral color for a calming retreat that is balanced. This fail-safe color also pairs well with sage greens and gray blues for a coastal aesthetic.

name: WHISPER
description: Whisper color is one of our most popular bright, warm whites and part of our Whites collection. Try Whisper as a wall, trim or accent color just about anywhere you want a shot of white inside or outside the home.

name: SWISS COFFEE
description: Swiss Coffee color is a warm white with creamy undertones and part of the Whites Collection. As one of our legacy colors that has been part of Dunn-Edwards history for decades, Swiss Coffee adds just the right amount of warmth while still feeling neutral and crisp. This neutral white is a customer favorite, for good reason. The color of fresh cream, Swiss Coffee is a casual, soft white that is versatile and adds a sense of depth when paired with lighter or darker neutrals.

name: BABY'S BREATH
description: Baby’s Breath is a subtle, natural warm white and part of our Whites Collection. With a hint of delicate freshness, this effortless white color is versatile and an ideal choice for almost any design style. Pair Baby’s Breath with sage and tan for a classic color palette.

name: PEARL NECKLACE
description: Pearl Necklace is a light, pearlescent warm white and part of our Whites Collection. Like grandmother’s pearls, this sophisticated and versatile white color is a classic and always in style. Add Pearl Necklace throughout the home to create a clean, quiet wash of color that serves as a lovely backdrop for art and décor.

name: FROSTING CREAM
description: Frosting Cream color is a bright, warm white and part of our Whites collection. Try Frosting Cream as a whole home hue for an elegant, sleek look to your space to allow freedom to design in a far-reaching range of styles.

name: SWAN WHITE
description: Swan White paint color is a soft, luminous off-white with warm undertones that bring a sense of subtle elegance. Its creamy brightness makes it an ideal backdrop for both classic and contemporary interiors, enhancing natural light and complementing a wide range of palettes.

name: ANTIQUE WHITE
description: Antique White paint color is an inviting white with a soft greige undertone. This weathered white is an ideal wall color for almost any design style to create an elegant statement. The subtle depth of this white pairs well with soft greens and warm grays.

name: MILK GLASS
description: Milk Glass color is a warm, bright white perfect for creating a polished and fresh look. A designer-favorite, Milk Glass is a great choice for trim and ceilings paired with soft neutrals for coastal, light-filled charm.

name: PINK LILY
description: Pink Lily is a light, whitened red-violet color and part of the Reds Collection. Inspired by the blooming pink lily flowers on full display in spring time, paint Pink Lily in a cozy reading room and layer in lighter neutrals like cream and natural wood tones. Balance with charcoal gray or gray-blues. For the adventurous, paint Pink Lily in a powder room and pair with navy blue and antique brass fixtures.

name: DEEP MAGENTA
description: Deep Magenta is a dark purplish-red, inspired by its origins in Magenta, Italy, in the 19th-century. During this time a dye named fuchsine was discovered from the fuchsia plant and the color became a success, used widely in fashion and art. Magenta is trending through 2022 so try this dramatic hue in a space that you want others to notice.

name: MAHOGANY CHERRY
description: Mahogany Cherry is a deep, plum rose hue exuding warmth and nostalgia. This burgundy, inspired by sweet cherries, is perfect for treasured spaces as the color's intensity will create a cozy, welcoming aesthetic. Pair with terracotta, warm neutrals and soft whites for an enriching color experience.

name: PRETTY IN PINK
description: Pretty in Pink paint is a light fuchsia rose color and part of our Reds Collection. Inspired by the range of sweet, nursery pinks and popular pink shades of Mid-century Modern design, this shade of pink will brighten any room. Try Pretty in Pink paired with bold, abstract art, black and white textiles and a Moroccan rug for a bohemian vision.

name: RAZZLE DAZZLE
description: Razzle Dazzle color is a vibrant, bold magenta color with a hint of purple, Razzle Dazzle is energetic and playful. It brings a sense of excitement and drama, making it perfect for making a statement or adding a pop of color to bold, creative designs.

name: CHERRY BERRY
description: Deep and deliciously distinguished, Cherry Berry is a magenta petal pink paint color.

name: FAIRY DUST
description: Fairy Dust color is a light, whitened magenta pink and part of our Reds Collection. Sparkling and light, add a touch of fairytale magic to a nursery, powder room, guest space or other interior spaces that need a wisp of color.

name: PINK PUNCH
description: Pink Punch color is a vivid fuchsia and part of our Reds collection. This confident, cheerful hue is perfect for tropical design styles and looks great as an accent color in powder rooms, entryways, and front doors for a fun, bright welcome.

name: MERLOT
description: Upscale yet celebratory, Merlot is a toast for your walls. This classic wine paint color infused hue adds versatility to a variety of different design styles.

name: BALLET SLIPPER
description: Ballet Slipper color is a sweet and light, bright pink and part of our Reds Collection. Inspired by the classic shoe worn by ballerinas everywhere, try Ballet Slipper in a nursery or guest room for a burst of pastel freshness or even a front door for an invigorating welcome.

name: ROUGE
description: Rouge color is a midtone dusty cedar red and part of our Oranges Collection. Inspired by the makeup used to tint a person's cheeks, Rouge is a lovely warm hue perfect for a powder room, guest bedroom or even a front door.

name: PALE JASPER
description: This soft and whimsical pink paint color will make you smile. Like the color of fluffy cotton candy, Pale Jasper is so cheerful and delicate, perfect for adding a touch of sweetness to your home.

name: CEDAR GROVE
description: Cedar Grove color is a rich, burnt coral that feels earthy and rustic. This deep terracotta, with a hint of red, is reminiscent of cedar wood and sun-warmed clay tile. Incorporate this color into Southwestern or Mediterranean designs to bring depth to a neutral color palette.

name: IRON ORE
description: Iron Ore is a rich, earthy terracotta color with deep red and brown undertones. This grounded shade recalls the raw, weathered strength of natural iron deposits and traditional clay materials.

name: FRESH CANTALOUPE
description: Fresh Cantaloupe color is a bright coral orange and part of our Oranges Collection. This refreshing color is a perfect choice for the kitchen or breakfast nook walls to brighten the space.

name: TANGERINE DREAM
description: Tangerine Dream is a bright orange and part of our Oranges and Tans collection. Inspired by the variety of fruit available through the seasons to enjoy. As a vivid hue, try Tangerine Dream where you want a happy spot of color on your home interior or in commercial spaces such as restaurants and retail shops.

name: PALE APRICOT
description: Pale Apricot color is a light, whitened orange hue and part of our Oranges collection. Pair Pale Apricot with a soft gray-green and warm white for a pastel-infused room palette.

name: NECTARINE
description: Nectarine color is a bright, citrus orange hue and part of our Oranges Collection. Fresh off the tree and ready to to use on interior spaces, try Nectarine in a powder room, dining room or other space where a zesty spark of bold color is needed to wake up a room.

name: BUTTERMILK
description: Buttermilk color is a light, bright pastel yellow and part of our Yellows Collection. Inspired by the baker's go-to ingredients for biscuits, buttermilk adds a bit of warmth and tang. Try Buttermilk in a guest room, children's room or as an accent where you need a bright lift to the space. Buttermilk is also a perfect addition to your Cottagecore color palette.

name: VIBRANT HONEY
description: Vibrant Honey is a deep, ambered-yellow and part of our Yellows collection. Inspired by the delicious variety of honey from local farms, try this happy hue in a playroom, workout space, or any area needing a bit of sunshine.

name: RICH IVORY
description: Rich Ivory paint color is a light sun-kissed yellow color and part of our Yellows Collection. Inspired by a variety of fresh light yellow flowers in spring bouquets, Rich Ivory is a brighter, happy hue perfect for kitchens and breakfast nooks to welcome the start of a new day. Pair with gray blues and whites for a fresh, balanced palette.

name: PARCHMENT PAPER
description: Parchment Paper color is a tinted white with orange-yellow undertones and is part of our Yellows Collection. Did you know there’s a National Parchment Day? This light and bright hue showcases the best in traditional designs and is a perfect option for Cottage styles.

name: BISCUIT
description: Biscuit color is a light, golden yellow and part of our Yellows collection. For a brighter and lighter golden hint of color, try Biscuit in any interior room for a spot of sunshine.

name: GINGERBREAD HOUSE
description: Gingerbread House is a brassy, ambered gold and part of our Yellows Collection. Inspired by the treasured holiday activity of making gingerbread houses, try this hue in a dining room or den for a cozy atmosphere paired with warm woods and accents.

name: AZTEC AURA
description: Aztec Aura is a light, bright honey golden yellow with orange undertones. Inspired by the mystique and historical lore of the American West, this hue is a lovely spot of refreshing color to create a friendly, sunny space. Pair with warm whites and neutrals for a cozy cottage retreat style.

name: HONEY GLOW
description: Your walls are glowing (well, they will be)! Worthy of becoming a Dunn-Edwards Color of the Year, this warm, golden yellow paint color with orange notes gives an air of playfulness and style to any space.

name: MILITARY GREEN
description: Military Green color is a midtone olive green and part of our Greens collection. Try this hue on cabinetry or built-ins for a refreshingly updated look to the home.

name: LIGHT PINE
description: Light Pine is a muted, natural green with a touch of yellow color and part of the Greens Collection. Inspired by the sights and smells of pine trees found in our local mountains, Light Pine is a calming hue that can act as a neutral in almost any room. Paint kitchen cabinetry in Light Pine and pair with cream on the walls and a touch of pink accents for a charming, cottagecore influence in the kitchen.

name: EARLY HARVEST
description: Watch your walls spring to life with this fresh avocado green paint color. Organic and natural, Early Harvest imparts a soft and casual look, making it an excellent companion for many different design styles.

name: MINT JULEP
description: Mint Julep is a light and bright, citrus lime green color and part of our Greens Collection. Vivacious and invigorating and inspired by the classic Southern cocktail, pair Mint Julep with hot pink and cool white for a zesty, fashion-inspired color palette.

name: OLIVE MARTINI
description: Live the good life with this light, vintage olive green paint color. Olive Martini is a natural, relaxed and organic green that lends a sense of effortless style.

name: SILENT BREATH
description: Silent Breath is a crisp and cool, light seafoam green color with a hint of blue and part of our Blues Collection. Clean and fresh, this color is a breath of fresh air and balances well with beachy sand tones and sky blues for airy, reflective spaces that restore and rejuvenate.

name: ECOLOGICAL
description: Get ready to be enchanted. This woodland forest green paint color shaded with gray is a classic color.

name: SPEARMINT
description: Spearmint color is a light, bright pastel green-blue and part of our Blues Collection. Exuding icy cool and crisp freshness, Spearmint is a dazzling and cheerful color that can trigger creativity and a sense of refreshing lightness. Try Spearmint in a work space, loft or front door to welcome visitors. Spearmint is also a perfect color to add to your Mid-century home color palette.

name: AQUA BLOOM
description: Aqua Bloom is a light, bright aqua blue and part of our Blues Collection. Inspired by island surf, Aqua Bloom is a cheerful paint hue that's perfect for a beach home or guest house retreat to create an aqua color vacation vibe.

name: SEAPORT
description: Everything feels like smooth sailing with this subdued seafoam blue paint color.

name: BLUE MOON
description: This refreshing, misted light blue paint color is bright and cheerful. With a peaceful, yet energized feel, Blue Moon is the perfect color for many different design styles, making it so rare it only comes around once in a- well, you get the idea.

name: MYSTERIOUS BLUE
description: Is it blue, or is it blue-green? Is it historic or future-forward? This majestic peacock blue paint color is full of mystery and intrigue. Sophisticated and timeless, Mysterious Blue is a perfect accent color anywhere in your home.

name: AFTER THE STORM
description: After the Storm color is a deep, moody teal with strong blue-green undertones, reminiscent of the sky just after a heavy rain. Its rich, calming hue evokes a sense of tranquility and resilience, making it an ideal choice for creating a serene yet dramatic atmosphere in both modern and nature-inspired designs.

name: BLUE SPRUCE
description: Clean and calm, Blue Spruce is a classic frosted blue forest paint color. This delicate hue looks great inside or outside and it harmonizes with many different design styles.

name: PERIWINKLE
description: Periwinkle color is a lavender blue and part of our Purples/Violets collection. Inspired by the wide variety of wildflowers that dot the landscape in spring, including periwinkle, try this midtone, twilight hue in an area of your home where calm is priority.

name: BOSSA NOVA BLUE
description: Bossa Nova Blue color is a deep, grayed periwinkle and part of our Purples Collection. Inspired by the famous Bossa Nova music of Brazil, try Bossa Nova Blue in a guest room or library to add a quiet, complex spot of color for relaxation.

name: PALE SHALE
description: Pale Shale color is an icy periwinkle hue and part of our Purples Collection. Inspired by the colors of natural sediment including quartz, Pale Shale is a soft, calm color perfect for spas, guest rooms or nurseries.

name: LONDON FOG
description: London Fog color is a midtone grayed-periwinkle and part of our Purples collection. Inspired by a deep winter fog that settles in as thick as a London evening at the shore – worthy of an evening spent with a classic Charles Dickens novel such as "The Christmas Carol." Try London Fog in a dressing room or powder for a sophisticated swath of color that will play as a lush neutral against other design elements.

name: PENCIL LEAD
description: Pencil Lead color is a dark slate with primarily dark blue tones with a subtle touch of violet and part of our Purples Collection. With dramatic flair, this color is a great choice for an entertainment room or restaurant to add a moody, engaging atmosphere.

name: ICY LAVENDER
description: Icy Lavender color is a cool, delicate shade of pale lavender with soft gray undertones, giving it a frosty, ethereal quality. Its subtle lavender tones are balanced by a hint of cool gray, making it both soothing and sophisticated. Icy Lavender is perfect for creating serene, minimalist spaces, and it pairs beautifully with soft whites, muted pastels, or deeper shades of gray to add depth and elegance to any room.

name: GRAPHITE
description: Graphite color is a dark grayed-purple and part of our Purples collection. This deep, mysterious hue layers on a moody backdrop with dramatic flair—perfect for maximalist designs.

name: DUSK
description: Dusk color is a light, whitened lavender and part of our Purples/Violets collection. This soft hue is inspired by the receding light of a late fall day with lavenders, oranges, pinks and yellows disappearing into the dark of night. Try Dusk in a bedroom, office or even your meditation area as a soothing, calming backdrop.

name: VIOLET GEMS
description: Violet Gems is a pastel purple color with a subtle blue undertone and part of our Purples Collection. Infused with a dose of calming energy, lavenders such as Violet Gems are trending upwards as a replacement to Millennial Pink. Try Violet Gems in a guest room for a subtle touch of glam.

name: VIOLET CRUSH
description: Sweet and curious, Violet Crush beckons us to explore imaginary lands and fanciful tales. This delicate purple paint color with a whisper of blue is both soft and playful, teeming with whimsical charm.

name: PLAYFUL PURPLE
description: Playful Purple is a light purple with a subtle blue undertone color and part of the Purples Collection. With a joyful and creative spirit, create a stylish statement by painting Playful Purple in bedrooms for a delightful backdrop to a cottage or bohemian design aesthetic. Pair with moss greens and sky blues for instant charm.

name: LINGERING LILAC
description: This light, feathery dusted purple paint color is like a bouquet for your wall. Nurture imagination and peaceful energy with the cool purple of Lingering Lilac.

name: RED CONTRAST
description: This bright, fruit punch red paint color makes a bold and vibrant statement anywhere it goes. Dramatic, energized and traditional, it looks beautiful inside or out.

name: GOLDENROD
description: Goldenrod color is a golden yellow with orange undertones and part of our Accents Collection. Inspired by the goldenrod flowering plant, this hue feels like a sunny, summer day. Pair with other saturated colors like chocolate brown, sapphire blue and emerald green for a sophisticated, rich scheme for a formal space such as a dining room or restaurant.

name: LIME TWIST
description: Lime Twist color is a bright, zesty yellow-green that exudes energy and freshness. Its lively, citrusy hue adds a playful and bold touch, perfect for creating vibrant, eye-catching spaces or adding a pop of color to modern designs.

name: IN THE TROPICS
description: In the Tropics is a bright, saturated, almost fluorescent lime green paint color. Showcase your modern or island-style decor with this energetic accent color that makes a big impact.

name: SPRING JUNIPER
description: Spring Juniper color is a deep, ivy green and part of our Accents collection. Inspired by the variety of juniper trees growing in the American West, try Spring Juniper in the formal living space to add drama punctuated by lots of molding treatments and layers of fabrics or in a restaurant that highlights indoor/outdoor dining.

name: LUCKY CLOVER
description: Wealthy and playful, this leafy, jungle green paint color brings an abundance of color. Lucky Clover looks great anywhere you want to summon good fortune.

name: TEAL WATERS
description: Teal Waters is a deep teal green color with a touch of blue and part of our Accents Collection. Inspired by the deep-sea waterways, pair Teal Waters with gold and white for a chic color palette in a living room.

name: RARE TURQUOISE
description: Rare Turquoise is a dark, aquatic, mineral shade of blue-green and part of our Accents Collection. At once uplifting and calming, try Rare Turquoise as a statement color in a living room, dining room, on kitchen cabinets, libraries, dressing rooms, baths and even bedrooms. Pair with neutrals to balance out the boldness of the hue.

name: AQUATIC
description: Aquatic color is a deep turquoise blue and part of our Accents Collection. Dreamy and mysterious, Aquatic makes a dramatic statement as an accent color on cabinetry and walls throughout the home and exudes color confidence when used on the front door.

name: DEEP OCEAN
description: Deep Ocean color is a dark, marine blue with a touch of green undertones and part of our Accents collection. Evoking the mysteries of the ocean depths, Deep Ocean is a sophisticated choice for a whole room maximum impact.

name: BEAUTIFUL BLUE
description: If you're looking for a wow-factor, this is it. Beautiful Blue is a vivid, cobalt blue paint color that is bright and saturated, giving it a bold and playful feel.

name: INDIGO NIGHT
description: Indigo Night color is a deep, sapphire blue and is part of our Accents collection. This deep blue is a perfect backdrop to both traditional and modern styles. Try Indigo Night on your kitchen cabinets for added drama.

name: PURPLE ODYSSEY
description: It's time for an adventure! Purple Odyssey is a lush, saturated royal purple paint color. This vibrant purple will transform your home and open up a new set of design possibilities.

name: SCARLET APPLE
description: Scarlet Apple color is a deep, scarlet red and part of our Accents collection. Inspired by the beautiful red apples harvested in the fall, try Scarlet Apple on the front door for a welcoming entry or in a candy shop as a vivid backdrop to all the delicious treats on display.

name: NORTHERN TERRITORY
description: Give your space a sense of adventure with Northern Territory. This sophisticated, natural deep brown paint color that has subtle orange undertones.

name: RICH MOCHA
description: Rich Mocha color is a dark brown and part of our Accents collection. Inspired by the perfect drink on a chilly day. Try Rich Mocha as an exterior accent or full body at a lakeside cabin for a punch of color that blends with the natural surrounding landscape.

name: AMAZING AMETHYST
description: This earthy plum paint color with a hint of red, Amazing Amethyst offers a sophisticated splendor that feels both elegant and masculine.

name: BOHEMIAN JAZZ
description: Summon the feeling of a turn of the century club with all of its smoky splendor and intrigue. Bohemian Jazz is a dusty, mid-tone plum paint color that feels sophisticated and timeless.

name: OUTER BOUNDARY
description: Outer Boundary color is a dark, rich brown with a subtle hint of plum. The warmth and depth of this color will make a space feel cozy and grounded, while still bringing a luxurious feeling to any design. Pair with dusty pink and olive green for a fun, vintage vibe.

name: ANTIQUE GARNET
description: Dusky red paint color with subdued plum undertones will turn any home into an instant classic. Add a touch of drama and sophistication with this moody, vintage hue.

name: DARK RUBY
description: Dark Ruby color is a deep, earthy red and part of our Warm Neutrals Collection. Adding depth and color as an alternative to traditional neutrals, Dark Ruby adds complex energy to a space. Dark Ruby pairs well with other earthy neutrals and can add a vintage touch in living rooms and dining rooms. Architecturally, Dark Ruby adds a beautiful touch of warmth for your mountain cabin hideaway.

name: PALE BERRIES
description: Inspired by the softly stained cream of strawberry shortcake, Pale Berries is a delicate, wispy rose taupe paint color. This warm purple gives any space a comfortable, casual feeling.

name: PLUSH SUEDE
description: Plush Suede is a midtone rosy brown color and part of our Warm Neutrals Collection. With the touch of rose and it's warm tones, Plush Suede gives a sense of luxury and is perfect for entertainment spaces such as dining and living rooms. Pair with a muted pink and restful green to elevate the space.

name: CHOCOLATE MILK
description: Your walls will slurp up this cozy color! Chocolate Milk is a light taupe paint color that feels playful and casual. This warm neutral works well with many different design styles.

name: RIVER ROCKS
description: A dark taupe paint color chalked with a touch of gray, River Rocks feels naturally sophisticated and easy. It is a deeply soothing brown that works well with a Modern Farmhouse or Vintage Library aesthetic.

name: BLACK WALNUT
description: Black Walnut is a dark blackened brown color with a hint of red undertones and part of the Warm Neutrals Collection. Evoking the smoky richness of the natural black walnut tree, this hue is ideal for interiors and exteriors. Pair with cool whites and lighter taupes for a monochrome color palette.

name: DESERT ROCK
description: Soft taupe brown paint color with a hint of red and yellow, this warm neutral evokes a natural and cozy feeling.

name: ANTIQUE PAPER
description: Antique Paper is a subtle off-white color with a hint of green and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. With a slightly warmer appearance and less gray infusions, this color sets the scene for adding other sand hues and soft influences of nature to create harmony and balance within a home. Pair with darker greiges, butter and sage for the influence of Cottagecore aesthetic.

name: CRYSTAL HAZE
description: Crystal Haze is a light greige color with a touch of green undertone and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. Timeless and classic, try Crystal Haze as a whole home color that will work with any design aesthetic.

name: POROUS STONE
description: Porous Stone is a grounded light warm gray color dusted with green and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. Inspired by nature, this timeless neutral color feels sophisticated yet harmonious with almost any design style. Pair with sage green and sky blue for a beachside cottage color palette.

name: FLINTSTONE
description: Flintstone is a midtone mossy greige color with a hint of green and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. Reminiscent of a shifting landscape, this color is a versatile neutral that works well in almost every environment and is ideal for exteriors, doors, trim work and kitchen cabinetry. Pair with neutral whites, leathers and warm woods for a touch of bohemian aesthetic.

name: FOSSIL
description: Fossil color is a light, whitened taupe gray and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. This light, cool color is a great choice for contemporary spaces such as lofts and modern, beach homes to bounce off the natural light.

name: FOGGY DAY
description: Foggy Day color is a light, misty warm gray with a hint of green and part of our Cool Neutrals collection. Inspired by the cool wintry days, blanketed by fog and mist. Foggy Day is a sophisticated neutral and easy to bring into the interiors, complementing a variety of other colors in both warm and cool tones.

name: MUSLIN
description: Muslin color is a light warm greige with a slight green undertone and part of our Cool Neutrals collection. This effortlessly stylish neutral works well with many design styles and pairs well with both cool and warm color palettes.

name: PLAY ON GRAY
description: Play on Gray is a mid tone warm gray color with a tinge of green and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. This timeless shade of gray has endless appeal with a variety of design styles. Pair Play on Gray with rust and cream for a traditional interior or exterior color scheme.

name: CALICO ROCK
description: Embrace the organic lifestyle. Calico Rock is a dusty green-gray paint color. This timeless and sophisticated cool neutral brings the great outdoors to you.

name: CENTER RIDGE
description: Center Ridge is a deep, earthy warm gray-green with a touch of yellow with an enriching, comfortable quality. Organic and nature-inspired, Center Ridge is a splendid choice for modern and bungalow home styles. Pair with other light, muted gray-greens for a monochromatic touch or add a splash of apricot and lemon for true outdoor inspiration.

name: LIMESTONE
description: Limestone color is a light stone gray-green and part of our Cool Neutrals collection. A classic, well-balanced neutral that goes with any design style, try Limestone on the exterior or interior of your home paired with other richer greens and neutrals for classic elegance.

name: SERENE THOUGHT
description: Serene Thought paint color is a muted warm gray with a touch of olive green. Its understated earthy tone creates a soft look and is perfect as a backdrop for vintage-inspired designs.

name: LATTE FROTH
description: Latte Froth color is a delicate, creamy off-white with a touch of warmth, reminiscent of frothy milk in a latte. This light and airy color is ideal for brightening up spaces and adding a subtle, sophisticated elegance to any room.

name: GREEN SCENE
description: This earthy green paint color washed with yellow gives any space an organic, traditional look.

name: WISHING WELL
description: Wishing Well is a subtle, sagebrush green color with a hint of gray and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. Make a wish! Wishing Well is an ideal color choice to set a casual design aesthetic for interiors or exteriors. Pair with warm whites and deeper sage greens for a hint of monochromatic desert aesthetic.

name: IVY GARDEN
description: Ivy Garden color is a dark, aged gray-green and part of our Cool Neutrals collection. Inspired by mature gardens overgrown with ivy, try Ivy Garden on a shed or guesthouse to blend in with the natural landscape.

name: DOVE'S WING
description: Dove’s Wing is an airy, soft off-white color with a tinge of green-gray undertone and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. Soothing and calming, this color is ideal for any space in the home. Incorporate Dove’s Wing with subtle shades of green and muted grays for a tranquil color palette.

name: ANTIQUE COIN
description: Antique Coin paint color is a soft, muted gray-green reminiscent of the patina found on ancient copper coins. This weathered hue adds an understated elegance to a color palette with warmer tones and symbolizes the beauty of imperfection.

name: PEBBLE WALK
description: Sophisticated and moody, elegant and versatile, this muted green-gray paint color looks great in any room. Pebble Walk pairs well with almost any design style.

name: BURNT CRIMSON
description: Dark and dramatic, Burnt Crimson is a deep, mahogany red wood paint color. It feels distinguished with a slight edge, like a work of classic fiction that spins an intriguing tale.

name: ROSEWOOD
description: Rosewood color is a deep, rosy-brown and part of our Classics collection. Try this hue on desert modern, Ranch and Craftsman style homes for an infusion of desert sunset color inspiration.

name: PEACH
description: Peach is a muted, light orange color and part of the Classics Collection. Soft, airy, and quietly joyful, Peach adds a sense of contentment and warmth to any wall it graces and can act as a neutral. Try Peach in a kitchen paired with blush tones and white trim for a classic cottage aesthetic. Or for a Mid-century modern vibe, pair with another pastel like mint green or sky blue.

name: BRIAR
description: Briar color is a dark brown and part of our Classics collection. Briar celebrates National Teddy Bear Day and honors the history of one of childhood’s favorite toys and Briar's Bears are especially collectible. Try Briar on the exterior of a traditional home or ADU unit for a dramatic hue that will also blend with the surrounding natural landscape.

name: ROMAN BRICK
description: Get grounded and centered with this warm, organic neutral. Roman Brick is a mid-tone brown paint color with a trace of chestnut, giving it a hint of spice and dramatic flair.

name: SANDAL
description: Sandal is a midtone warm neutral and part of our Classics Collection. As a longtime designer favorite, Sandal is a great choice as a body color on Spanish, Craftsman and other traditional architecture styles. It also works well as a whole home base wall color throughout the home for flexibility when designing the rooms.

name: STONISH BEIGE
description: Achieve effortless comfort by adorning your home with this faded clay paint color with a wisp of red and yellow. This warm neutral has a casual, timeless feel that makes it perfect for almost any design style and place in your home.

name: BAKED POTATO
description: Baked Potato is a medium, rich shade of beige color with subtle touch of red and part of our Classics Collection. Seasoned just right, Baked Potato is an ideal color choice for traditional interior or exterior spaces. Pair with warm whites and cooling blues for a classic, traditional color palette.

name: MESA TAN
description: Mesa Tan color is a midtone warm brown with red undertones and part of our Classics Collection. This warm neutral paint with timeless appeal is a great addition to an exterior Spanish-Mediterranean color scheme.

name: CHAMPAGNE
description: Champagne is a warm, creamy ivory hue and part of our Classics collection. Inspired by the beverage shared during life's many celebrations, try Champagne on the interior or exterior of a traditional style home for an easy, classic update.

name: SPANISH WHITE
description: Spanish White is a light warm white color with a touch of cream and part of our Classics Collection. As a legacy color of ours, Spanish White speaks to the rich history of the Southwest. Paint the exterior of a Spanish style home for a touch of elegance.

name: ADOBE
description: Adobe color is an earthy, warm desert neutral and part of our Classics collection. Inspired by historic desert dwellings, try Adobe on your desert modern, Spanish or Pueblo home for a warm, classic look.

name: MADERA
description: Madera is a midtone ivory color with a touch of brown and part of our Classics Collection. As a legacy color, Madera adds classic charm to a space. Pair with sage greens and sky blues for a cottage aesthetic.

name: JASMINE
description: Jasmine color is a light, bright and airy yellow and is part of our Classics collection. As a refreshingly light hue, this is a great color to try for spring in your home.

name: FLAXEN
description: Flaxen is a light warm ivory and part of our Classics collection. Inspired by the color of straw, the color Flax was first noted as a color name in 1915 and an early use of flaxen to describe hair color was in the book David Copperfield by Charles Dickens. Try this light hue through your traditional style home for a spot of warmth.

name: FLAXSEED
description: Flaxseed color is a light ivory and part of our Classics Collection. Inspired by its namesake, flaxseed, this warm hue is perfect in a kitchen or bath of a cottage for a cheerful update.

name: TRAVERTINE
description: Travertine color is a midtone warm neutral with slight pink undertones and part of our Classics Collection. Inspired by the natural stone used in so many homes, try Travertine as a neutral base throughout the interior or exterior of a traditional style home paired with blues or greens and chocolate browns for classic color palette.

name: SANDCASTLE
description: Sandcastle is an eggshell warm neutral color and part of our Classics Collection. As easy as a day on the beach, Sandcastle looks great in every room, as well as on exterior spaces. This classic, relaxing color pairs well with Coastal design styles and is a perfect backdrop to the treasures in your home.

name: BONE WHITE
description: Bone White color is a light, neutral, warm off-white and part of our Classics collection. As a perfect choice for a whole home color as it infuses a hint of warmth through the space, pair with other Warm Neutrals for traditional elegance or with soft blues and greens for a coastal ambiance.

name: CAMEO
description: Cameo color is a creamy ivory neutral and part of our Classics collection. Inspired by the jewelry with material that is carved with a raised relief that often depicts a profile of a face or a mythical scene. Cameo works well in a wide range of design styles from cottage to Spanish, so try Cameo as a warm, soft backdrop to accent hues throughout your traditional style home.

name: HIGH NOON
description: High Noon color is a warm, golden beige that captures the soft, glowing light of midday sun. This inviting and versatile shade brings a touch of radiance and comfort to a space, creating a cozy and welcoming atmosphere.

name: CHAPARRAL
description: Chaparral color is a sun-washed beige with subtle hints of sand and peach, inspired by the dry, golden landscapes of the American West. Its soft warmth adds an inviting and effortless elegance to interiors and exteriors.

name: APACHE TAN
description: Apache Tan color is a warm, earthy beige with hints of peach, offering a cozy and inviting feel. This color is perfect for creating a welcoming and comforting ambiance in both residential and commercial spaces.

name: SAHARA
description: Sahara is a medium toned, oatmeal beige color and part of our Classics Collection. Comfortable and classic, Sahara will wrap your walls in coziness. Pair with warm whites and cinnamon reds for a sense of casual, Cottagecore vibes.

name: OYSTER
description: Oyster color is a light, warm neutral and part of our Classics Collection. Did you know there’s a National Oyster Day and that there are over 100 different species of oysters? This neutral is a lovely backdrop to complement warmer color palettes throughout the home, light and inviting.

name: LINEN WHITE
description: Linen White is a creamy off-white color with gentle beige undertones that suggest the softness of natural textiles. Its subtle warmth makes it an ideal choice for creating light, inviting spaces with a classic touch.

name: BISON BEIGE
description: Bison Beige is a midtone desert taupe color with a touch of green undertone and part of the Classics Collection. Embrace your rugged impulses with a warm putty shade perfect for those looking for a warm gray color. Classically pastoral, this endlessly versatile color feels right at home with rustic ranch and French country design styles.

name: ASH GRAY
description: Ash Gray is a weathered, warm gray color with rosy undertones and part of our Classics Collection. Classic and versatile, this color adds a sophisticated, stylish note to Bohemian and desert modern design aesthetics. Pair Ash Gray with warm whites and navy for a classic color palette.

name: BIRCHWOOD
description: Birchwood is a light warm neutral with a touch of gray and part of our Classics Collection. This color exudes a casual and comfortable feeling and with its versatility, is perfect for Transitional and Rustic Ranch design styles. Pair with moss greens and deep chocolate for a space reflective of nature and the indoor/outdoor lifestyle.

name: ALMOND
description: Almond is a light warm beige hue and part of our Classics collection. Inspired by one of the most popular nuts for summer salads and other dishes here in the Southwest, try Almond in a guest room to envelop the room in classic comfort.

name: WEATHERED BROWN
description: Weathered Brown is a deep brown and part of the Classics Collection. Add a sense of depth and sophistication with this dark, almost-graphite brown that is also a historically-accurate color. Weathered Brown is an ashy, blackened brown that elevates the drama of any space while also grounding it. These rare qualities make it the perfect companion for Mid Century Modern, Rustic Ranch, Craftsman, and Arts & Crafts design styles.

name: RINCON COVE
description: Rincon Cove color is a soft, muted taupe that blends warm beige and cool gray tones. This elegant and versatile shade brings a sense of calm and understated sophistication to any interior, creating a welcoming and balanced ambiance.

name: CASHMERE
description: Cashmere color is a light creamy neutral with pink undertones and is part of our Classics collection. Inspired by this favorite material for sweaters and throws — soft and luxurious.

name: HICKORY
description: Hickory color is a warm neutral and part of our Classics Collection. Inspired by the hickory tree and its changing leaf colors through fall season, Hickory is a perfect color for interiors and exteriors of traditional style homes.

name: ROSE MAUVE
description: Rose Mauve is a faded, aged rose color and part of our Then, Now & Forever® Collection. As a historic color noted from our Victorian era research, Rose Mauve is an elegant, subtle hue that can act as a neutral. Try it in a bedroom to give a welcoming, restful atmosphere.

name: CALIFORNIA DREAMIN'
description: Muted grape paint color with a wash of gray, California Dreamin' evokes the splendor of vineyards in the morning mist. Use this earthy purple as a grounding element that hints at happier days ahead.

name: FOLKLORE
description: Folklore color is a deep, muted reddish-brown shade that evokes warmth and earthiness. It carries a vintage, rustic feel, reminiscent of aged leather or autumn leaves. This color is versatile in design, offering a grounded and rich backdrop for natural or vintage-inspired themes.

name: LA VIE EN ROSE
description: The color of heirloom roses or the perfect pink sunset over Paris, La Vie en Rose captures a sense of romanticism and innocence.

name: LADY IN RED
description: Lady in Red is a strong, classic red with yellow undertones and one of our historically-accurate hues of the Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by vintage images showing Victorian-era women wearing red capes and gowns, especially during the holidays, Lady in Red is a perfect red for classic front door appeal.

name: RED CRAFT
description: This crisp apple red paint color brings with it an appreciation for all things hand-crafted and expertly made. Bright, bold, and traditional, it imparts the rich color of bricks while adding a touch of history.

name: ROSE DE MAI
description: Named after the French rose that only blooms in May, Rose de Mai is a dusty, tea rose paint color that feels romantic and distinguished.

name: CITY OF PINK ANGELS
description: Bask in comfort and class with this soft pink paint color. A more traditional version of the hue, it has been found in historic Spanish Colonial Missions and Italianate Victorian buildings, but it also feels right at home.

name: GYPSUM ROSE
description: Gypsum Rose is a soft, blush beige color with peach undertones, offering a warm and understated look. Taking its name from the rose-like formations of crystal clusters of gypsum found in deserts throughout the world, this muted sandy color adds an earthy feel to any design.

name: COGNAC
description: This amber-infused orange was a popular earthy orange and noted in the Harrison Bros & Co Town & Country card during the Victorian Era and was referenced in other architectural style research documents. During the Prohibition years in the 1920s, speakeasies provided a way for the party crowd to still drink. The Sidecar, one of the Prohibition Era's most popular drinks included Cognac, Cointreau, and lemon juice.

name: MONARCH MIGRATION
description: Found in historic Victorian and Arts & Crafts homes, this orange ochre paint color is an earthy hue that was named for the monarch butterfly migration that happens along the West Coast each fall.

name: HARRISON RUST
description: Harrison Rust is a dark brick-brown, rust orange and one of the historic colors in our Then, Now & Forever® Collection. As a historic hue discovered on Victorian architecture, this is a great color for Victorians, Craftsman and Spanish style homes. As an interior-only color, this moody hue is perfect for accent walls, dining rooms and theater rooms to add drama.

name: SONOMA CHARDONNAY
description: Sonoma Chardonnay color is a grassy yellow inspired by the legendary wine region of Sonoma County, California. This historically-accurate color is referenced in our Victorian and International research. Try Sonoma Chardonnay in the foyer or kitchen for a refreshingly bright spot of color.

name: OCHRE REVIVAL
description: This ochre yellow paint color brings a bit of levity to classic design styles such as Victorian, Italianate, 20th Century Revival, Arts & Crafts, Craftsman, Art Deco and Spanish Mediterranean. This hue brightens up any room while adding a sense of historical significance.

name: MAIZE
description: A muted, mid-tone yellow paint color, Maize is the color of nostalgia. Imagine simpler, more prosperous times with this historically-accurate hue that has been found in Arts & Crafts, Victorian, Italianate, 20th Century Mission Revival, and Art Deco buildings.

name: ZUCCHINI FLOWER
description: Like a fresh golden orange zucchini flower from the garden, Zucchini Flower paint color is cheerful and energizing, adding a touch of vibrancy to your walls.

name: BUNGALOW GOLD
description: With all the splendor of a bronze statue, Bungalow Gold is a deep burnished gold paint color that comes off as very dramatic.

name: WILDFLOWER HONEY
description: Comforting and sweet, Wildflower Honey is a warm, rich honey paint color with an organic feel.

name: PRAIRIE LAND
description: You can almost hear the tall yellow grass blowing in the breeze with this organic, warm neutral. Prairie Land is a yellow paint color with a touch of spring green undertones, creating an endlessly comfortable feel.

name: LAZY DAISY
description: Lazy Daisy color is a warm, soft shade of pale yellow with creamy, buttery undertones. This color evokes a cheerful, sunny feel, like the gentle warmth of a spring morning. Lazy Daisy has a subtle, nostalgic charm, reminiscent of blooming wildflowers, making it ideal for adding a touch of warmth and joy to rooms while maintaining a light and airy aesthetic. It pairs beautifully with other soft neutrals or earthy tones for a fresh, uplifting look.

name: SUNNYSIDE UP
description: Bring the sunshine in! This cheerful sunflower yellow paint color will energize any room with a bold splash of color. Found in historic Victorian buildings.

name: HUNTINGTON GARDEN
description: Huntington Garden color is a soft, natural shade of green with earthy undertones, Huntington Garden brings to mind lush gardens and serene landscapes. It is a calming, organic color that evokes feelings of tranquility and growth, perfect for creating a refreshing, nature-inspired ambiance.

name: DESERT SAGE
description: Desert Sage color is part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection. As one of our historic colors, it was identified at the J Mora Moss Cottage, a Gothic Revival era home. The desert and prairies of the American West come alive in spring with a wide variety of sage. Try this hue on a classic Spanish-Mediterranean or Ranch home on kitchen cabinets and molding for a classic soft, green accent.

name: GOTHIC REVIVAL GREEN
description: Gothic Revival Green color is a rich citron green with a touch of yellow, that adds a botanical feeling to any color palette. Found on 19th century Gothic Revival Architecture, this color works well as an accent to deep, dark hues and was often used to highlight intricate details in a design.

name: WINE GOBLET
description: This dramatic red paint color with notes of oak adds a touch of sophistication and mystery wherever it goes. Inviting and cozy, yet upscale and timeless, its deep red and purple undertones make it an excellent choice for many different design styles.

name: MAUVE-A-LISH
description: This dark mauve feels at once earthy and romantic. Luxuriate in this luscious, muted berry paint color and pair it with Bohemian, Moroccan, Craftsman, and Arts & Crafts design styles. This dark mauve feels at once earthy and romantic. Luxuriate in this luscious, muted berry tone.

name: PURPLE PROSE
description: Purple Prose is a dark plum paint color that feels dramatic and edgy with an aura of timelessness. Nuanced and poetic, its slight purple undertone lends well to sophisticated interiors and dark, romantic designs styles.

name: NIGHTSHADE
description: Nightshade color is a deep eggplant hue and part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by one of the species of flowering plants in the nightshade family as well as the eggplant, also in the nightshade family, this gorgeous, deep hue pairs great with a variety of greens or corals for a real punch of color.

name: PINK DAHLIA
description: Pink Dahlia is a saturated, plush magenta pink inspired by classic, formal gardens filled with ornately petaled dahlia flowers. Decadent and cheerful, Pink Dahlia is a wonderful choice to create excitement at the entry. Pair with crisp whites and cool grays for modern flair.

name: LE CORBUSIER CRUSH
description: Don't be shy. This bright, bold color is full of energy while still feeling classic and handsome. Le Corbusier Crush is a modern, masculine red-orange paint color that adds a touch of vibrancy to many different design styles.

name: BARN RED
description: At once classic and rustic, you can dress this color up or down. Barn Red is a deep red paint color with a hint of black.

name: ROYAL RED FLUSH
description: Royal Red Flush is a rich, ruby red color and part of our Then, Now & Forever® Collection. A bold, striking hue, try Royal Red Flush on a front door, or in an entryway, dining room, theater or lounge space for a show stopping statement.

name: VINTAGE RED
description: Vintage Red color is a rich, deep red with warm, muted undertones, evoking the timeless appeal of classic heirlooms. Its slightly aged, earthy hue brings a sense of nostalgia and warmth, making it perfect for traditional or rustic designs with a bold, elegant touch.

name: OK CORAL
description: Energize your space with this true tropical coral paint color that has a slightly muted look.

name: POTTERY CLAY
description: Pottery Clay is a dusty coral hue that symbolizes the many shades of orange glazes found on Southwestern and Indian pottery, created by generations of artists in the American West. Friendly and inviting, Pottery Clay says "Our door's always open" in a cheerful nod to the neighborhood.

name: SPICE OF LIFE
description: Spice of Life color is a deep auburn red hue with orange undertones and as part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection, was noted as our 2019 Color of the Year. Try this strong, enticing, spice-market blend hue in a guest room or dining room for a bold statement. And to read more about Spice of Life, click here.

name: RED MAPLE LEAF
description: Muted and slightly grayed out, Red Maple Leaf paint color is dark and dramatic with just a hint of restraint. It is traditional and naturally influenced, making it compatible with a wide range of design styles.

name: CITRUS NOTES
description: Citrus Notes is a zesty, refreshingly bright orange and the perfect hue greet your visitors with the friendliest, cheerful welcome. As a color with power, pair Citrus Notes with warm neutrals and sage greens to bring nature's influence into your space.

name: ARIZONA CLAY
description: Like an earthen Saltillo tile, Arizona Clay is a natural, organic orange paint color.

name: THAT'S ATOMIC
description: Take a trip back to the sixties with this lively vintage green washed paint color with yellow.

name: LICHEN GREEN
description: Lichen Green color is a misty gray-green and part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by the variety of lichens found in California and the American West, try this hue as a body color throughout a traditional style home or on the exterior of a traditional Craftsman, Victorian or Spanish-Mediterranean style home to blend with the surrounding natural landscape.

name: MORRO BAY
description: Upscale meets nautical. This whale fin blue paint color is an instant classic. Relaxed yet tidy, Morro Bay will inspire you to - seas - the day with a refreshing splash.

name: DARK ENGINE
description: Dark Engine is a deep, chic black with a touch of violet and blue. For bold impact with a stylish touch, Dark Engine is an ideal choice for the entry. Pair with crisp white for a timeless, black and white color palette.

name: IGLOO
description: Igloo color is an icy, crisp white with cool undertones, evoking the serene beauty of snowy northern retreats. This bright white shines in contemporary and transitional spaces, making it perfect as a backdrop or standalone color. Ideal for kitchen cabinetry, Igloo pairs beautifully with marble and aged bronze accents to create a clean, fresh aesthetic.

name: ANTIQUE PAPER
description: Antique Paper is a subtle off-white color with a hint of green and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. With a slightly warmer appearance and less gray infusions, this color sets the scene for adding other sand hues and soft influences of nature to create harmony and balance within a home. Pair with darker greiges, butter and sage for the influence of Cottagecore aesthetic.

name: MUSLIN
description: Muslin color is a light warm greige with a slight green undertone and part of our Cool Neutrals collection. This effortlessly stylish neutral works well with many design styles and pairs well with both cool and warm color palettes.

name: BABY SEAL
description: Baby Seal color is a cool, medium gray with subtle blue undertones, evoking a sense of calm and understated elegance. This versatile shade is perfect for adding a touch of modern sophistication to both interior and exterior spaces.

name: COVERED IN PLATINUM
description: Covered in Platinum is a midtone, cool metal gray color and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. This soft medium gray color isn’t too blue, purple or brown and is an ideal choice for both interiors and exteriors for an inviting aesthetic. Widely versatile, Covered in Platinum suits almost any accent color, whether crisp whites, pastels or vivid, jewel tones.

name: SMOKE & ASH
description: Smoke & Ash is a muted, midtone grayed green color and part of the Then, Now & Forever® Collection. As a historic color, this hue is inspired by the historic droughts of California, resulting in wildfires, returning later in a rebirth of new life and greenery. Pair Smoke & Ash with whites, deep blues and beiges for a cozy farmhouse aesthetic.

name: FOSSIL
description: Fossil color is a light, whitened taupe gray and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. This light, cool color is a great choice for contemporary spaces such as lofts and modern, beach homes to bounce off the natural light.

name: NOMADIC TAUPE
description: Nomadic Taupe is a medium toned buff color and part of our Warm Neutrals Collection. Classic and versatile, this effortlessly elegant color works well in most design styles. Pair Nomadic Taupe with olive greens and rust reds for a classic, traditional exterior color palette.

name: SO CHIC!
description: So Chic! Is a light whitened gray with a touch of green and part of the Then, Now & Forever® Collection. This gray color never goes out of style and is flexible to use with a vast array of color schemes. So Chic! is a cool, light neutral gray that feels sleek and timeless. Use it wherever you want to add a bit of understated bling. Try So Chic! as a whole home body color for a modern touch.

name: COOL DECEMBER
description: Cool December color is a cooler, bright white and part of our Whites collection. Try Cool December on modern and contemporary dwellings for a crisp, clean look.

name: SOOT
description: Soot color is a dark charcoal gray and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the remains of time spent in the winter by the fireplace, Soot is a great choice for a front door, accent or even a modern exterior as part of the trend of dark colors on exteriors.

name: BISON BEIGE
description: Bison Beige is a midtone desert taupe color with a touch of green undertone and part of the Classics Collection. Embrace your rugged impulses with a warm putty shade perfect for those looking for a warm gray color. Classically pastoral, this endlessly versatile color feels right at home with rustic ranch and French country design styles.

name: SWISS COFFEE
description: Swiss Coffee color is a warm white with creamy undertones and part of the Whites Collection. As one of our legacy colors that has been part of Dunn-Edwards history for decades, Swiss Coffee adds just the right amount of warmth while still feeling neutral and crisp. This neutral white is a customer favorite, for good reason. The color of fresh cream, Swiss Coffee is a casual, soft white that is versatile and adds a sense of depth when paired with lighter or darker neutrals.

name: WHISPER
description: Whisper color is one of our most popular bright, warm whites and part of our Whites collection. Try Whisper as a wall, trim or accent color just about anywhere you want a shot of white inside or outside the home.

name: CLASSIC WHITE
description: Classic White is a cooler, neutral white color and is part of our High Hide Whites Collection. Inspired by classic elegance and clean architecture, Classic White is a snowy white color and the ideal neutral shade for bright and airy spaces and is a perfect blank canvas for art-filled spaces. This cool white color is illuminating and pure, making it an ideal white color for whole home design or for use on trim, ceilings and cabinetry.

name: STUCCO TAN
description: This soft, warm neutral is perfect for subtle, all over color. Stucco Tan is a whitened greige paint color that has a calming effect.

name: CRISP MUSLIN
description: Crisp Muslin color is a warm, delicate gray-beige (greige) and part of the Warm Neutrals Collection. This timeless, elegant neutral looks great in every room and is perfect for a variety of design styles.

name: WHISPER GRAY
description: Whisper Gray color is white-washed gray and part of the Classics Collection. Whisper Gray gives any room an airy, museum-like crispness when paired with a slightly lighter or darker contrasting color. It makes the perfect showcase for any style of furniture or artwork.

name: TRITE WHITE
description: Trite White is a warm, off-white and part of our Warm Neutrals collection. Inspired by the common use of whites as a neutral background to other colors, Trite White pairs well with pastels and brights as a subtle backdrop.

name: CLASSIC WHITE
description: Classic White is a cooler, neutral white color and is part of our High Hide Whites Collection. Inspired by classic elegance and clean architecture, Classic White is a snowy white color and the ideal neutral shade for bright and airy spaces and is a perfect blank canvas for art-filled spaces. This cool white color is illuminating and pure, making it an ideal white color for whole home design or for use on trim, ceilings and cabinetry.

name: NIGHTSHADE
description: Nightshade color is a deep eggplant hue and part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by one of the species of flowering plants in the nightshade family as well as the eggplant, also in the nightshade family, this gorgeous, deep hue pairs great with a variety of greens or corals for a real punch of color.

name: STAR OF PERSIA
description: Star of Persia is a lavish, amethyst-violet will be the star of your home. Inspired by its floral namesake, Star of Persia is a magical, ornamental color that will create high impact. Pair with sage green, sky blue and crisp white for a cottagecore delight.

name: SENTIMENTAL
description: Sentimental is a lush hyacinth purple with refreshingly, friendly tones that makes it a great front door color choice to welcome guests. A hint of blue makes Sentimental an updated vision of periwinkle and a perfectly elegant accent color to soft yellows, crisp whites and grass greens.

name: ENGLISH VIOLET
description: English Violet is a deep, complex purple ready for its dramatic entrance. With a touch of blue undertones, the dark, complex, enigmatic hue, inspired by its namesake is striking when paired with gray-blues and seafoam greens for a moody, Regencycore effect.

name: PEPPY PURPLE
description: Peppy Purple is a confident, upbeat and attention-getting hue is for its front door close up! With its red undertones, Peppy Purple complements deep olive and pine greens and stands out when paired with a variety of warm and cool neutrals.

name: PARISIAN PLUM
description: Parisian Plum is a sophisticated, warm purple with red undertones inspired by the juicy fruit of its namesake. Regal and classic, Parisian Plum is very au courant and glamorous though it’s a hue that transcends trends. Pair with olive greens, chartreuse, marigold, dark beige and grays for luscious, old-world refinement.

name: MULBERRY
description: Mulberry color is a deep, dark dried plum hue and part of our Accents collection. Inspired by the mulberry trees ripe with mulberry fruit, try this color in an entertainment area of the home or a lounge space in a commercial setting to complete a scene of sophisticated drama.

name: IN A MAROON MOOD
description: In a Maroon Mood is a warm, relaxing and thoughtful subtle brownish-red with hints of autumn vibes. A classic, grounding hue that exudes sophistication and natural earthiness, In a Maroon Mood is a versatile shade that pairs well with neutrals, as well as golden yellows, greens and blues.

name: WINE TASTING
description: Wine Tasting is a deep, muted violet-purple with mauve undertones that exudes luxury and coziness. A perfect hue for those looking to try a fresh color but not go too bold. Inspired by the wide range of red wines harvested each fall, Wine Tasting creates a refined mood when paired with golds and greens.

name: MAHOGANY CHERRY
description: Mahogany Cherry is a deep, plum rose hue exuding warmth and nostalgia. This burgundy, inspired by sweet cherries, is perfect for treasured spaces as the color's intensity will create a cozy, welcoming aesthetic. Pair with terracotta, warm neutrals and soft whites for an enriching color experience.

name: CHERRY HARVEST
description: Cherry Harvest is a dark, garnet red with a touch of blue undertones and denotes a thoughtful sensibility. As a lush, dark pink-red inspired by juicy cherries, Cherry Harvest pairs well with richer neutrals, as well as deeper wood tones for a touch of luxury.

name: JAIPUR DREAM
description: Jaipur Dream is a saturated rosy pink inspired by the beautiful city Jaipur. With its touches of pink and violet, the hue is no wallflower. This rich, elegant color generates buzz when paired with soft greens, taupes, warm neutrals and reddish brown tones.

name: NEON PINK
description: Neon Pink is a bold, dynamic and stimulating shade of pink for the adventurous spirits who wish to create a wow factor at the entry. With its slight yellow undertones, Neon Pink looks great when paired with crisp white, a pale pink for a monochromatic scheme or a light blue for a cooling balance.

name: SPANISH CARMINE
description: Spanish Carmine is a bold and striking, rich warm red favored by those who wish to make a statement. As a cousin to the more purplish and ruby carmine shades, Spanish Carmine is inspired by the range of reds processed using the historical methods of extraction from cochineal insects. As an energetic, passionate color, Spanish Carmine pairs well with creams, warm neutrals an gray-blues for an eye-catching appearance.

name: RESPLENDENT ROSE
description: Resplendent Rose is a lush, rosy pink hue inspired by the fragrant roses in summer bloom. Elegant and welcoming, Resplendent Rose provides a graceful touch to the entry and pairs well with other rich neutrals, as well as dusty pinks, sage and blue-grays for a homage to nostalgia.

name: CANDY CRUSH
description: Candy Crush is a vibrant, scarlet red hue inspired by the sweet, sugary treats and is a flawless choice for making a bold, energetic color statement. With its touch of orange, Candy Crush pairs well with olive greens, warm beiges and chocolates for an earthy palette or corals, yellows and sky blues for a bolder touch to keep you inspired.

name: RED-Y FOR FUN
description: Red-y for Fun is a rich, vivid cardinal red that radiates energy and life. Inspired by the power of play and action, Red-y for Fun is a captivating hue that pairs well with umbers, olives, and teals for an eclectic palette or crisp whites and brilliant blues for a touch of traditional, summery bright cottage flair.

name: SPIKED PUNCH
description: Spiked Punch is a brilliant raspberry, pinkish-red that is a chic and playful color choice for the front door. Inspired by fruity, summery cocktails, this grown up shade of pink gives off high energy and sophistication with a bit of an edge, making it a perfect choice for traditional or modern design aesthetics.

name: PINK DAHLIA
description: Pink Dahlia is a saturated, plush magenta pink inspired by classic, formal gardens filled with ornately petaled dahlia flowers. Decadent and cheerful, Pink Dahlia is a wonderful choice to create excitement at the entry. Pair with crisp whites and cool grays for modern flair.

name: BERRY RICHE
description: Berry Riche is a dusty rose pink with overtures of optimism and romance. Inspired by the favored summer pastime of picking berries, Berry Riche is a warm, earthy, muted pink is sweet without feeling too saccharine and pairs well with greens, blues, crisp whites and charcoal grays for wide appeal.

name: BERRY INSPIRED
description: Berry Inspired is a deep magenta that imbues the dramatic qualities of red and the indulgence of violet. This lush cranberry hue is inspired by the power of red and the introspection of purple and perfect as a welcoming front door color. Pair with neutrals and cool whites for classic charm.

name: ROSE APOTHECARY
description: Rose Apothecary is a refined, dusty rose with subdued, grayish overtures. Inspired by traditional shop fronts of times past, cottagecore and rural fantasy aficionados will love the nostalgic, romantic qualities and timeless elegance. Pair with warm neutrals, soft blues and greens for an inviting space.

name: CRUSHING ON CORAL
description: Crushing on Coral is an energetic, bronzed pink with undertones of orange. Inspired by a love of oceanlife and its colorful ecosystem, and as one of the most appealing shades, Crushing on Coral works well with a variety of design styles and adds comfort, warmth and optimism.

name: CORAL CHARISMA
description: Coral Charisma is a vivid, warm and life-affirming shade of orange-pink with a playful spirit. Inspired by the elusive and delicate life beneath the oceans, Coral Charisma adds a dramatic pop of color to any space. Pair with pinks, magentas, golden yellows and taupes for a desert sunset-inspired palette.

name: POTTERY CLAY
description: Pottery Clay is a dusty coral hue that symbolizes the many shades of orange glazes found on Southwestern and Indian pottery, created by generations of artists in the American West. Friendly and inviting, Pottery Clay says "Our door's always open" in a cheerful nod to the neighborhood.

name: AMARANTH
description: Amaranth is a reddish-rose and a representation of the color of the flower of the amaranth plant. The color is derived from the name in Greek mythology of a flower that was believed to never die that grew in the abode of the Greek gods on Mount Olympus. Amaranth is a statement-making hue that pairs well with most neutrals. Add lime and turquoise for a tropical vacation ambiance.

name: CHILES DE ARBOL
description: Chiles de Arbol is a spicy, vibrant red with orange overtones highlighting the complexity of the this hue. Inspired by the smoky chile with serious heat popular in Mexican and Thai cuisine, Chiles de Arbol is a fearless choice for the front door. Add a zest of lime and warm neutrals for a color palette that sparkles.

name: LADY IN RED
description: Lady in Red is a strong, classic red with yellow undertones and one of our historically-accurate hues of the Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by vintage images showing Victorian-era women wearing red capes and gowns, especially during the holidays, Lady in Red is a perfect red for classic front door appeal.

name: VERMILION
description: Vermilion is a brilliant orange-red and influenced by the color, color family, and pigment most often derived, since antiquity until the 19th-century, from the powdered mineral cinnabar. Bold and fierce, Vermilion is the perfect hue to make a dazzling, memorable entry.

name: CITRUS NOTES
description: Citrus Notes is a zesty, refreshingly bright orange and the perfect hue greet your visitors with the friendliest, cheerful welcome. As a color with power, pair Citrus Notes with warm neutrals and sage greens to bring nature's influence into your space.

name: PUMPKIN SPICE LATTE
description: Pumpkin Spice Latte is a spicy, autumnal yellow-orange inspired one of our favorite flavors that defines the fall season. For a palette that's pumpkin, spice and everything nice, pair Pumpkin Spice Latte with cinnamon browns, creamy neutrals and terracotta for a nature-infused, enchanting palette.

name: SMOOTH LIKE BUTTER
description: Smooth Like Butter is a sweetly churned, muted yellow that comforts and soothes. Inspired by one of life's small pleasures of adding a little butter to a meal, this hue is perfectly sunny welcoming touch to the home and an instant mood-booster. Smooth Like Butter is strong enough to stand on its own as an alternative to beiges and tans, or try pairing with gray blues and warm whites for a seaside cottage palette.

name: ZESTY YELLOW
description: Zesty Yellow is a bright, sunny yellow that dazzles the senses. Inspired by the infusion of yellows into 2020s trend palettes, Zesty Yellow is a perfectly vivid yellow to brighten the entry with happiness. Pair with rosy pinks, grass greens and sky blues for a cottagecore dream.

name: LEMON CURRY
description: Lemon Curry is a midtone, spicy yellow-green with chartreuse undertones. Inspired by the delicous yellow curries with dustings of turmeric to create the gorgeous, complex color, Lemon Curry is a visual treat that energizes a space. Pair with crisp whites and tinted blacks for a modern, graphic style or rich grays for French countryside charm.

name: LEMON MACARON
description: Lemon Macaron is a lively, bright yellow with a sunny disposition and a splendid choice to create a welcoming space. Save room for dessert with this sweetly inspired delight! Pair with coral, ocean blue and emerald green for Palm Springs vacation inspiration.

name: BOURBON SWEET TEA
description: Bourbon Sweet Tea is a perfectly brewed blend of amber and honey gold warmth inspired by the Southern soul-warming bourbon cocktail. Relaxing Southern charm is at play when choosing Bourbon Sweet Tea to grace your front door. Pair with iced yellows, lime greens and rich warm neutrals for a calming, traditional palette.

name: AZTEC AURA
description: Aztec Aura is a light, bright honey golden yellow with orange undertones. Inspired by the mystique and historical lore of the American West, this hue is a lovely spot of refreshing color to create a friendly, sunny space. Pair with warm whites and neutrals for a cozy cottage retreat style.

name: DESERT LIME
description: Desert Lime is a zesty, fresh citrus yellow-green perfect for those who desire an eye-catching, energizing spot of color. Inspired by the citrus fruit loved for its refreshing addition to spicy dishes, pair Desert Lime with light blush pinks and whites with Mid-century decor and brass accents for zippy appeal.

name: GRASSY KNOLL
