description: Grassy Knoll is a refreshing, revitalizing shade of green reminiscent of new beginnings and is perfect for those who have a love of nature and the great outdoors. With its yellow undertones, this shade of green is quite versatile and pairs with a wide variety of neutrals for a grounding effect, to a range of jewel tones and darker hues for a moody effect.

name: AMAZON PARROT
description: Amazon Parrot is a midtone, lush grassy green with a subtle yellow undertone inspired by the beautiful, endangered yellow-headed amazon parrots. With its strong ties to nature, this shade of green is perfect for those who invite the outdoors in. Pair with yellows and warm neutrals for fresh appeal.

name: SLIGHTLY JADED
description: Slightly Jaded is a darker, muted emerald green with distinguished, luxury appeal. Inspired by the range of jewel tone jade greens and play on words of the saying 'slightly jaded,' this hue speaks to opulence and tradition. Pair with rich warm neutrals for classic elegance or crisp whites and charcoal for a modern, graphic cottage aesthetic.

name: PUNCHY PERIDOT
description: Punchy Peridot is a luxurious, midtone jewel tone green that conveys an upscale sense of style. Inspired by the rarer, darker emerald peridot gemstones, this hue radiates affluence. Pair with rich warm neutrals for timeless grandeur or crisp whites and coral for a tropical palette.

name: SUMMER SEAGRASS
description: Summer Seagrass is a cool, calming grassy green with a touch of blue. Inspired by the underwater seagrass meadow habitats in shallow waters off land in seas around the world. Try Summer Seagrass as a main home hue or pair with other neutrals for a relaxing, coastal vibe. Or pair with vibrant yellows, pinks and blues for a youthful, punchy palette.

name: GINKGO LEAF
description: Ginkgo Leaf is a cool, refreshing seaglass green with a slight yellow undertone. Inspired by the fan-shaped ginkgo leaf, this hue represents health and longevity. Create a healthy environment by instilling Ginkgo Leaf into the home with other soft, muted neutrals for a relaxing retreat.

name: VERDIGRIS GREEN
description: Verdigris Green is a deep, lavish emerald green inspired by an Old French term, vert-de-Grèce (“green of Greece”) and for hundreds of years, verdigris was the most brilliant green readily available to painters. With such grand historical ties, Verdigris Green is enjoying a renaissance with its vibrant personality. Pair with copper and crisp white to energize a space.

name: MALACHITE GREEN
description: Malachite Green is a vivid, bluish-green and inspired by the malachite gemstone with its banded striations of green. With an air of elegance and sophistication, Malachite Green looks harmonious with turquoise and other greens, as well as accents of violet and spicy orange for a rich, maximalist palette.

name: DANCE TEAL DAWN
description: Dance Teal Dawn is a dark, blackened bluish-green with an alluring, moody quality. This dreamy hue reminiscent of the sea is the perfect choice for a colorful, chic space paired with splashes of gold.

name: DAY IN THE SHADE
description: Day in the Shade is a deep, intense jungle green with a touch of blue that invokes references of lush tropical rainforests. Make an unexpected statement with Day in the Shade paired with golds, whites and navy blues for an inspiring, jewel-toned palette.

name: VERDE NICE
description: Verde Nice is a richly-saturated jewel green that envelopes one in a soothing, mysterious embrace. A perfect hue for welcoming visitors, pair Verde Nice with deep blues, wine and amethyst for a classic autumnal palette.

name: HI TECH TURQUOISE
description: Hi Tech Turquoise is an invigorating blue-green with global appeal. The aquatic influences energize and beckon one to escape to a tropical paradise. For those who love beach life, Hi Tech Turquoise sets the surf and sand mood with a vibrant welcoming entry. Pair with warm sand, seaglass and white to complete the coastal style.

name: COME TO COSTA RICA
description: Come to Costa Rica is a invigorating, yet serene turquoise hue that brings thoughts of tropical waters, wellbeing and an escape from the everyday life. A perfect color for those seeking a daily pop of tropical color to welcome them back home! With both warm and cool tones, Come to Costa Rica is a vivid splash of color against warm neutrals or a perfect color to pair with deep blues and crisp white for a classic maritime scheme.

name: SIREN SONG
description: Siren Song is a vivacious, aqua blue with a hint of green that recalls the lore of Greek mythology and the song of the siren that would lure sailors with their hypnotic sound. Bold with nautical references, Siren Song beckons to show off the front door with happiness. Pair with corals, yellows and sand to complete a coastal palette.

name: BALINESE RETREAT
description: Balinese Retreat is a refreshing splash of turquoise that enchants the senses with tropical vibes. Crisp and cool, this saturated hue brings a dose of joyful color to the entry. Pair with crisp white, mellow yellow and coral for an enjoyable vacation palette.

name: AGE OF AQUARIUS
description: Age of Aquarius is a bright, cyan blue with a splash of green ready for summer poolside fun. This mood-lifting hue adds a punch of vitality to the entry. Pair with cherry red and crisp white for modern, graphic pop art intensity or with soft sand and warm white for a soothing, coastal aesthetic.

name: ISLAND HOP
description: Island Hop is a gorgeous, muted shade of aquamarine is ready for vacation to begin. With the soothing appeal of blue and invigorating allure of green, Island Hop represents an escape to far-off tropical destinations. Create a classic maritime palette by adding deeper blues, subtle gray and cool white or pair with warm neutrals for a classic, coastal escape.

name: BLUE IN BARBADOS
description: Blue in Barbados is a deep, aquamarine blue with a tinge of green that is ready to create a vacation atmosphere. Recreate tropical memories by pairing Blue in Barbados with jungle green, coral and soft sand. Or pair with crisp white and cool gray for a calming palette.

name: LA AT NIGHT
description: LA at Night is a deep, moody sea blue-green recalling the mysteries of the sky at night over the Pacific Ocean in Los Angeles. With its saturated shade enticing a midnight stroll by the ocean, LA at Night is a splendid hue for the entryway. Pair with neutral whites and warm greiges for a homage to coastal beauty.

name: KINETIC ENERGY
description: Kinetic Energy is a brilliantly vibrant ultramarine blue evocative of classic painter pigments. With its intensity, this hue is a superb choice for those who want the entry to stand out. Pair with sky blues, slate and sand for a classic beachside palette.

name: EMBOLDENED BLUE
description: Emboldened Blue is a deep sapphire that is a beguiling choice for those who seek a regal, time-honored front door color. With its trace of violet undertones, pair Emboldened Blue with gray-blue and cool white for a classic palette.

name: AM I BLUE?
description: Am I Blue? Is a deep cobalt blue with a touch of violet for added intrigue. Inspired by the classic song 'Am I Blue?' sung by pioneering music legend Ray Charles, this hue is a symphony of emotion and an exemplary choice for the front door. Pair with neutral whites and charcoal gray for timeless appeal.

name: FOLLOW MY BLUE BLISS
description: Follow My Blue Bliss is a deep, nautical blue that teleports one to a relaxing, seaside getaway. For the perpetual idealist, Follow My Blue Bliss conjures a mood of eternal summer vibes. Pair with deep slate, brighter turquoise and soft whites to complete a vacation palette of your dreams.

name: SUMMER AT THE SHORE
description: Summer at the Shore is a summery, ocean breeze blue aquamarine that is an ideal hue for relaxed beachside living. Pair with lemon yellows, sky blues, crisp whites and seafoam greens to complete the sunny season vacation palette.

name: HIMALAYAN BLUE POPPY
description: Himalayan Blue Poppy is an enchanting, light and clear sky blue with a touch of yellow. Inspired by the spectacular flower that puts on a show late spring through early summer, Himalayan Blue Poppy looks fresh and inviting as a front door color. Pair with sprightly yellows, pinks and greens for a botanic color palette.

name: MORE WATER PLEASE
description: More Water Please is a soothing, watery blue for those who wish to quench their thirst for color on the front door. Pair with cool, muted whites and neutrals for an homage to waterfront living.

name: SHORELINE DRIVE
description: Shoreline Drive is a lighter shade of classic blue that is calm and confident, perfect for those who seek a peaceful, elegant blue for the entry. Pair with other cool blues and warm neutrals for a thoughtful, meditative palette.

name: BERRY BERRY BLUE
description: Berry Berry Blue is a delectable, rich shade of blueberry blue with a touch of violet. This classic blue with a touch of grandeur is superb choice for those who love the richness of darker blue shades. Pair with warm whites, muted mauve and honey for a twist on tradition.

name: JODHPUR
description: Jodhpur is a rich, pigmented true blue with a tinge of violet that pays homage to the Blue City of Jodhpur, India. Steeped in history, experience a reminder of the city by painting the front door this lush shade of blue. Pair with cool neutrals and a subtle peach for meditative palette.

name: INDIGO WASH
description: Indigo Wash is a calming, stable and timeless deep shade of blue that an ideal choice for those who seek a classic and elegant front door color. With subtle red undertones, this hue takes on characteristics of a mysterious deep purple color. A classic pairing with indigo is crisp white and gray for a traditional scheme or pair with other blues for a monochromatic scheme.

name: STILL WATERS RUN DEEP
description: Still Waters Run Deep is a classic navy blue with traditional elegance and a nod to nautical. With a touch of violet, Still Waters Run Deep is a study in graceful refinement. Pair with crisp white and bright red for an Americana palette or with warm neutrals and coral as an updated twist on tradition.

name: CHARCOAL SMUDGE
description: Charcoal Smudge is a dark, charcoal gray with a hint of green undertone and part of our Cool Neutrals Collection. As a blend of gray and black, charcoal grays are very close to black but brighter and a sophisticated alternative to black for color palettes. Try Charcoal Smudge on an accent wall, in a powder room or on cabinetry for a dramatic effect.

name: REFINED GREEN
description: Refined Green is a deep, blackened green with a touch of blue that adds drama and intrigue. A bespoke, saturated hue with ties to the beauty of nature, Refined Green adds a comforting, cozy touch to the entry. Pair with off-whites and warm grays for timeless appeal.

name: DARK SHADOWS
description: Dark Shadows is a deep, blacked blue with a touch of green that can read as a complex black paint color with mysterious qualities. Rich and masculine, Dark Shadows adds a dignified perception to the front entry. Pair with warm neutrals and off-whites for a refined, restrained palette.

name: CENTER RIDGE
description: Center Ridge is a deep, earthy warm gray-green with a touch of yellow with an enriching, comfortable quality. Organic and nature-inspired, Center Ridge is a splendid choice for modern and bungalow home styles. Pair with other light, muted gray-greens for a monochromatic touch or add a splash of apricot and lemon for true outdoor inspiration.

name: ESPRESSO MACCHIATO
description: Espresso Macchiato is a deep, dark-roasted brown with a touch of red that envelopes the senses. Rich in character, Espresso Macchiato add drama to the entry. Pair with warm white and muted sage for a nod to the local coffee shop.

name: WINDING ROAD
description: Winding Road is a dark, concrete gray with a touch of violet that beckons one to the call of the open road. Moody and sophisticated, elevate your entry with Winding Road. Pair with subtle warm whites and beiges for a refined, masculine palette.

name: TOTAL ECLIPSE
description: Total Eclipse is a dark, complex black hue with green and blue undertones. Elevate your front entry with this enigmatic color to bring on the drama. Pair with light cool neutrals to complete this classic palette.

name: FADE TO BLACK
description: Fade to Black is a deep, dusty off-black with a touch of green and yellow undertones. Cinematically inspired, Fade to Black is an ideal color for an impactful entry. Pair with cool whites and neutrals for modern appeal.

name: DARK ENGINE
description: Dark Engine is a deep, chic black with a touch of violet and blue. For bold impact with a stylish touch, Dark Engine is an ideal choice for the entry. Pair with crisp white for a timeless, black and white color palette.

name: ROSE MAUVE
description: Rose Mauve is a faded, aged rose color and part of our Then, Now & Forever® Collection. As a historic color noted from our Victorian era research, Rose Mauve is an elegant, subtle hue that can act as a neutral. Try it in a bedroom to give a welcoming, restful atmosphere.

name: CALIFORNIA DREAMIN'
description: Muted grape paint color with a wash of gray, California Dreamin' evokes the splendor of vineyards in the morning mist. Use this earthy purple as a grounding element that hints at happier days ahead.

name: FOLKLORE
description: Folklore color is a deep, muted reddish-brown shade that evokes warmth and earthiness. It carries a vintage, rustic feel, reminiscent of aged leather or autumn leaves. This color is versatile in design, offering a grounded and rich backdrop for natural or vintage-inspired themes.

name: LA VIE EN ROSE
description: The color of heirloom roses or the perfect pink sunset over Paris, La Vie en Rose captures a sense of romanticism and innocence.

name: LADY IN RED
description: Lady in Red is a strong, classic red with yellow undertones and one of our historically-accurate hues of the Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by vintage images showing Victorian-era women wearing red capes and gowns, especially during the holidays, Lady in Red is a perfect red for classic front door appeal.

name: RED CRAFT
description: This crisp apple red paint color brings with it an appreciation for all things hand-crafted and expertly made. Bright, bold, and traditional, it imparts the rich color of bricks while adding a touch of history.

name: ROSE DE MAI
description: Named after the French rose that only blooms in May, Rose de Mai is a dusty, tea rose paint color that feels romantic and distinguished.

name: CITY OF PINK ANGELS
description: Bask in comfort and class with this soft pink paint color. A more traditional version of the hue, it has been found in historic Spanish Colonial Missions and Italianate Victorian buildings, but it also feels right at home.

name: GYPSUM ROSE
description: Gypsum Rose is a soft, blush beige color with peach undertones, offering a warm and understated look. Taking its name from the rose-like formations of crystal clusters of gypsum found in deserts throughout the world, this muted sandy color adds an earthy feel to any design.

name: COGNAC
description: This amber-infused orange was a popular earthy orange and noted in the Harrison Bros & Co Town & Country card during the Victorian Era and was referenced in other architectural style research documents. During the Prohibition years in the 1920s, speakeasies provided a way for the party crowd to still drink. The Sidecar, one of the Prohibition Era's most popular drinks included Cognac, Cointreau, and lemon juice.

name: MONARCH MIGRATION
description: Found in historic Victorian and Arts & Crafts homes, this orange ochre paint color is an earthy hue that was named for the monarch butterfly migration that happens along the West Coast each fall.

name: HARRISON RUST
description: Harrison Rust is a dark brick-brown, rust orange and one of the historic colors in our Then, Now & Forever® Collection. As a historic hue discovered on Victorian architecture, this is a great color for Victorians, Craftsman and Spanish style homes. As an interior-only color, this moody hue is perfect for accent walls, dining rooms and theater rooms to add drama.

name: SONOMA CHARDONNAY
description: Sonoma Chardonnay color is a grassy yellow inspired by the legendary wine region of Sonoma County, California. This historically-accurate color is referenced in our Victorian and International research. Try Sonoma Chardonnay in the foyer or kitchen for a refreshingly bright spot of color.

name: OCHRE REVIVAL
description: This ochre yellow paint color brings a bit of levity to classic design styles such as Victorian, Italianate, 20th Century Revival, Arts & Crafts, Craftsman, Art Deco and Spanish Mediterranean. This hue brightens up any room while adding a sense of historical significance.

name: MAIZE
description: A muted, mid-tone yellow paint color, Maize is the color of nostalgia. Imagine simpler, more prosperous times with this historically-accurate hue that has been found in Arts & Crafts, Victorian, Italianate, 20th Century Mission Revival, and Art Deco buildings.

name: ZUCCHINI FLOWER
description: Like a fresh golden orange zucchini flower from the garden, Zucchini Flower paint color is cheerful and energizing, adding a touch of vibrancy to your walls.

name: BUNGALOW GOLD
description: With all the splendor of a bronze statue, Bungalow Gold is a deep burnished gold paint color that comes off as very dramatic.

name: WILDFLOWER HONEY
description: Comforting and sweet, Wildflower Honey is a warm, rich honey paint color with an organic feel.

name: PRAIRIE LAND
description: You can almost hear the tall yellow grass blowing in the breeze with this organic, warm neutral. Prairie Land is a yellow paint color with a touch of spring green undertones, creating an endlessly comfortable feel.

name: LAZY DAISY
description: Lazy Daisy color is a warm, soft shade of pale yellow with creamy, buttery undertones. This color evokes a cheerful, sunny feel, like the gentle warmth of a spring morning. Lazy Daisy has a subtle, nostalgic charm, reminiscent of blooming wildflowers, making it ideal for adding a touch of warmth and joy to rooms while maintaining a light and airy aesthetic. It pairs beautifully with other soft neutrals or earthy tones for a fresh, uplifting look.

name: SUNNYSIDE UP
description: Bring the sunshine in! This cheerful sunflower yellow paint color will energize any room with a bold splash of color. Found in historic Victorian buildings.

name: HUNTINGTON GARDEN
description: Huntington Garden color is a soft, natural shade of green with earthy undertones, Huntington Garden brings to mind lush gardens and serene landscapes. It is a calming, organic color that evokes feelings of tranquility and growth, perfect for creating a refreshing, nature-inspired ambiance.

name: DESERT SAGE
description: Desert Sage color is part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection. As one of our historic colors, it was identified at the J Mora Moss Cottage, a Gothic Revival era home. The desert and prairies of the American West come alive in spring with a wide variety of sage. Try this hue on a classic Spanish-Mediterranean or Ranch home on kitchen cabinets and molding for a classic soft, green accent.

name: GOTHIC REVIVAL GREEN
description: Gothic Revival Green color is a rich citron green with a touch of yellow, that adds a botanical feeling to any color palette. Found on 19th century Gothic Revival Architecture, this color works well as an accent to deep, dark hues and was often used to highlight intricate details in a design.

name: WINE GOBLET
description: This dramatic red paint color with notes of oak adds a touch of sophistication and mystery wherever it goes. Inviting and cozy, yet upscale and timeless, its deep red and purple undertones make it an excellent choice for many different design styles.

name: MAUVE-A-LISH
description: This dark mauve feels at once earthy and romantic. Luxuriate in this luscious, muted berry paint color and pair it with Bohemian, Moroccan, Craftsman, and Arts & Crafts design styles. This dark mauve feels at once earthy and romantic. Luxuriate in this luscious, muted berry tone.

name: PURPLE PROSE
description: Purple Prose is a dark plum paint color that feels dramatic and edgy with an aura of timelessness. Nuanced and poetic, its slight purple undertone lends well to sophisticated interiors and dark, romantic designs styles.

name: NIGHTSHADE
description: Nightshade color is a deep eggplant hue and part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by one of the species of flowering plants in the nightshade family as well as the eggplant, also in the nightshade family, this gorgeous, deep hue pairs great with a variety of greens or corals for a real punch of color.

name: PINK DAHLIA
description: Pink Dahlia is a saturated, plush magenta pink inspired by classic, formal gardens filled with ornately petaled dahlia flowers. Decadent and cheerful, Pink Dahlia is a wonderful choice to create excitement at the entry. Pair with crisp whites and cool grays for modern flair.

name: LE CORBUSIER CRUSH
description: Don't be shy. This bright, bold color is full of energy while still feeling classic and handsome. Le Corbusier Crush is a modern, masculine red-orange paint color that adds a touch of vibrancy to many different design styles.

name: BARN RED
description: At once classic and rustic, you can dress this color up or down. Barn Red is a deep red paint color with a hint of black.

name: ROYAL RED FLUSH
description: Royal Red Flush is a rich, ruby red color and part of our Then, Now & Forever® Collection. A bold, striking hue, try Royal Red Flush on a front door, or in an entryway, dining room, theater or lounge space for a show stopping statement.

name: VINTAGE RED
description: Vintage Red color is a rich, deep red with warm, muted undertones, evoking the timeless appeal of classic heirlooms. Its slightly aged, earthy hue brings a sense of nostalgia and warmth, making it perfect for traditional or rustic designs with a bold, elegant touch.

name: OK CORAL
description: Energize your space with this true tropical coral paint color that has a slightly muted look.

name: POTTERY CLAY
description: Pottery Clay is a dusty coral hue that symbolizes the many shades of orange glazes found on Southwestern and Indian pottery, created by generations of artists in the American West. Friendly and inviting, Pottery Clay says "Our door's always open" in a cheerful nod to the neighborhood.

name: SPICE OF LIFE
description: Spice of Life color is a deep auburn red hue with orange undertones and as part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection, was noted as our 2019 Color of the Year. Try this strong, enticing, spice-market blend hue in a guest room or dining room for a bold statement. And to read more about Spice of Life, click here.

name: RED MAPLE LEAF
description: Muted and slightly grayed out, Red Maple Leaf paint color is dark and dramatic with just a hint of restraint. It is traditional and naturally influenced, making it compatible with a wide range of design styles.

name: CITRUS NOTES
description: Citrus Notes is a zesty, refreshingly bright orange and the perfect hue greet your visitors with the friendliest, cheerful welcome. As a color with power, pair Citrus Notes with warm neutrals and sage greens to bring nature's influence into your space.

name: ARIZONA CLAY
description: Like an earthen Saltillo tile, Arizona Clay is a natural, organic orange paint color.

name: THAT'S ATOMIC
description: Take a trip back to the sixties with this lively vintage green washed paint color with yellow.

name: GUNSMOKE
description: Gunsmoke is a smoky, gray-green color and part of our Then, Now & Forever® Collection. Inspired by the landscape colors of the American West frontier, Gunsmoke is a complex neutral that highlights gray, green and a touch of brown. Pair with tan and warm white for a classic home color palette.

name: LICHEN GREEN
description: Lichen Green color is a misty gray-green and part of our Then, Now & Forever® collection. Inspired by the variety of lichens found in California and the American West, try this hue as a body color throughout a traditional style home or on the exterior of a traditional Craftsman, Victorian or Spanish-Mediterranean style home to blend with the surrounding natural landscape.

name: WINTER TWIG
description: Winter Twig is a complex, versatile warm gray color with undertones of gray, green and brown and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Taking inspiration from winter strolls through the forest, Winter Twig is a cozy neutral color ideal for casual traditional and modern spaces.

name: LONG WINDING ROAD
description: Long Winding Road is a subtle, warm muted gray color with a hint of brown undertones and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A lovely choice to envelope one in color, Long Winding Road takes us on a journey to create a cozy, hushed atmosphere and is a perfect choice for modern living spaces.

name: MOONBEAM
description: Moonbeam is a warm and uplifting gray color with a hint of red and brown and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Look to the night sky and view the rays of moonlight as inspiration for this subtle and versatile neutral color. Pair Moonbeam with other cooler neutrals for an inviting, earthy palette or pair with crisp white and bolder hues for a modern, artistic aesthetic.

name: DUST YOURSELF OFF
description: Dust Yourself Off is a warm, lighter shade of gray color with a hint of brown and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. This versatile and easy-to-use neutral color is ideal for adding just the right amount of contrast to a space against crisp white trim, creatings a fresh, soothing space. And as an alternative to white, Dust Yourself Off is a restrained neutral that adds a touch of visual interest.

name: MUSHROOM FORAGING
description: Mushroom Foraging is an organic, midtone warm greige color with a touch of brown and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the classic, outdoor pursuit of foraging for mushrooms, this neutral color is a wonderful addition to a casually-chic space filled with rustic woods and stone elements.

name: SUBTLETY IS BEST
description: Subtlety is Best is a soft, chalky light gray color with a touch of violet and part of our New Neutrals Collection. When just a touch of color will do, Subtlety is Best is the ideal choice for interior spaces to create a dreamy oasis. Pair this color with sage green, ocean blue and coral for a beach cottage aesthetic.

name: BEACHWOOD DRIVE
description: Beachwood Drive color is a light, warm gray with a subtle hint of brown, offering a versatile and classic neutral tone. This adaptable color complements a variety of design styles, from modern to traditional. Inspired by the iconic Los Angeles street leading to a popular trail near the Hollywood sign, Beachwood Drive pairs beautifully with heirloom textiles and accents for a vintage-inspired aesthetic.

name: STAY CALM
description: Stay Calm is a clean, understated midtone gray color with a touch of brown and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A resourceful, balanced neutral color that inspires a relaxed atmosphere, Stay Calm is a lovely color choice for a many interior and exterior design styles.

name: FREE SPIRITED
description: Free Spirited is an airy, ultra-light shade of gray with a slightest hint of gray and brown and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. With just the subtlest hint of color, Free Spirited works well as both a wall and trim color to add depth to a space while still feeling light and airy. This is an ideal color choice for spaces calling out for a sophisticated and chic hue that is a versatile option to support a variety of design styles.

name: WIND IN THE WILLOWS
description: Wind in the Willows is a graceful, understated shade of gray color with a touch of violet and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the classic children's novel, "The Wind in the Willows," this muted gray color creates a calm backdrop to other colors or can stand on its own. Use in a kitchen or entertaining space to makes guests feel at home.

name: ZENNED OUT
description: Zenned Out is a rich, refined shade of gray color with a touch of red and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. A perfect addition to meditation spaces, Zenned Out is an understated color that creates a harmonious background to more vibrant accent colors, as well as other neutrals.

name: FIELDSTONE LODGE
description: Fieldstone Lodge is a natural, warm midtone gray color with a hint of green undertone and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Organic and timeless, Fieldstone Lodge is a color fit for cozy cabin spaces. Pair this soothing gray with whites and a bright spot of color for a classic interior design style.

name: GRAPHITE SKETCHES
description: Graphite Sketches is a saturated, concrete gray color with a touch of red and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Artistic pursuits influenced the creation of Graphite Sketches, and this color provides just the right amount of depth and drama as a backdrop to this drawing art medium. As an alternative to black or dark blue, this color can act as the perfect accent color without being intrusive.

name: HAZY GRAY
description: Hazy Gray is an adaptable and versatile midtone gray color with a touch of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the filtered shades of a hazy gray day, this color creates an elegant backdrop to both traditional and modern design styles. Pair with warm woods, woven materials and simple-patterned textiles for a sublime cottagecore aesthetic.

name: FAUX BOIS
description: Faux Bois is a versatile, light warm gray color with a hint of red and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the artistic craft of imitating wood grain and highly inspirational in the creation of whimsical furniture pieces, this organic neutral color is an ideal choice for casual spaces. Pair with other warm gray colors for a monochromatic color palette.

name: STONEWARE CLAY
description: Stoneware Clay is a light, neutral gray color with a touch of green and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the art of making pottery, Stoneware Clay is an organic-influenced neutral color that creates a restrained, elegant backdrop to any design style. For a serene, relaxing space, paint Stoneware Clay on the walls and pair with warm whites to complete the classic color palette.

name: HEART OF STONE
description: Heart of Stone is a light, warm gray color with a touch of green and violet undertones and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the classic phrase, "heart of stone," this versatile neutral color is an elegant choice for any design style and pairs well with a variety of accent hues including sage greens, muted blues and straw yellows. With its depth and balance of warmth and coolness, it is an inviting color choice for for exteriors as well.

name: DOVE'S CRY
description: Dove's Cry is a light warm gray color with a touch of green and violet undertones and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the classic call of the dove bird, this neutral color complements almost any color palette and makes a room feel cozy and comfortable.

name: COMFORT ZONE
description: Comfort Zone is a light, natural warm gray color with a touch of brown and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Easygoing and compatible with a variety of design styles, Comfort Zone is a color that make you feel cozy and comfortable in any space. Add to living and dining spaces as an invitation to guests to make them feel relaxed and want to stay for awhile.

name: YES IT'S GREIGE
description: Yes It's Greige is a light, warm greige color with a slight hint of brown and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. In case you were wondering, Yes It's Greige. This neutral color is an easy choice with its versatility and muted qualities. An essential option for wabi sabi design, pair this color with rustic materials and a minimalist layout to create a space of serenity.

name: ORGANIC GREIGE
description: Organic Greige is a natural, light warm greige color and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. With nature as its guide, Organic Greige pairs well with other organically-influence hues to create a serene, meditative space. Pair this color with charcoal gray and crisp white, along with stonework for a classic exterior color palette.

name: BONE DRY
description: Bone Dry is a light, chalky warm gray color with a touch of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Versatile enough to be used as a natural off-white, Bone Dry works effortlessly between traditional and modern design styles.

name: NATURAL PROCESS
description: Natural Process is an organic, lighter shade of greige color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Emanating warm and nurturing sensibilities, Natural Process invites a cozy and relaxed atmosphere and is an ideal color choice for timeless, understated design styles. Add warm, rustic woods and aged bronze elements for a touch of historic significance.

name: NATURALLY-SOURCED
description: Naturally-Sourced is a muted, lighter shade of warm gray color with a hint of green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Taking inspiration from organic materials and sustainable living, Naturally-Sourced is an all-purpose color that works well with almost any design style. For a timeless, traditional color palette, pair Naturally-Sourced with charcoal, muted green, soft blue and cool gray. Or create a warm minimalist palette by pairing with other warm neutrals, black, muted pink and putty.

name: SHALE STONE
description: Shale Stone is a saturated, midtone warm gray color with a touch of brown and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the beauty of sedimentary rock formations and natural deposits in a range of earthy hues, Shale Stone is an ideal color choice adaptable to a variety of design styles. Pair this color with moss green, navy blue, beige, rust and warm white for an earthy boho color palette.

name: WELL BALANCED
description: Well Balanced is an elegant midtone shade of warm greige color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. As a mantra for today's busy lifestyles, Well Balanced is an adaptable neutral color that works well with both warm and cool colors. Inviting and soothing, pair this color with putty, sand, warm white, brick and brighter coral for a modern, feminine-chic color palette.

name: COUNTRYSIDE
description: Countryside is a muted, dusty midtone warm gray color with a touch of smoky brown and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Reminiscent of a meadow after the rainfall, Countryside is a neutral color that complements almost any design style. Pair with ochre, brick, mineral blue and charcoal for a country cottage aesthetic.

name: HARE'S TAIL GRASS
description: Hare's Tail Grass is a graceful, medium shade of warm gray color with a hint of green undertones and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Also called bunnytail grass, this ornamental annual grass is a fun addition to any garden and provides inspiration for its namesake color. Pair Hare's Tail Grass with grassy greens and warm whites for an organic, neutral color palette.

name: PETRICHOR
description: Petrichor is a lighter, soft shade of warm greige color with a hint of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the pleasant smell that accompanies the first rain after a long period of warm, dry weather, Petrichor is a subtle color that creates an atmosphere of serenity. Pair Petrichor with whites, blues, greens and other neutrals for classic, timeless appeal.

name: SHAGGY DOG
description: Shaggy Dog is a darker shade of warm gray with subtle gray and brown tones and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Our furry friends provide inspiration for this color and Shaggy Dog is a classic choice for exteriors, cabinetry and trim work. Pair with charcoal, off-white, navy and deep forest green for a historic, masculine color palette.

name: FELDSPAR
description: Feldspar is a rich, midtone shade of warm gray color with a slight touch of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With its rich chemical composition and use in glassmaking and ceramics, the mineral Feldspar is an excellent representation of this color. A warm and inviting hue that invites conversation, pair Feldspar with creamy white and navy in a den for a luxe, cozy vibe.

name: PUMICE STONE
description: Pumice Stone is a vapor light gray color with a trace of yellow and green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With its subtlety and versatility, Pumice Stone is an ideal neutral color for almost any design style. Pair with white and charcoal in a laundry room or bathroom for a clean, modern aesthetic.

name: SYCAMORE BARK
description: Sycamore Bark is a lighter warm gray color with a hint of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With the beauty of its mottled bark in shades of greenish-white to brown and gray, Sycamore Bark is an ideal representation of this color. A sense of ease and comfort is created by pairing this color with other neutrals and creamy white for a meditative color palette.

name: ROOTED
description: Rooted is a chameleon-like, midtone warm gray color with a touch of brown and green undertones and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Capturing the rich history of centuries-old artifacts, Rooted is an ideal color for historic and classic architecture. Pair with navy, golden yellow and brick for a sense of grandeur with this color palette.

name: WELL-CRAFTED
description: Well-Crafted is an organic, lighter warm greige color with a hint of brown and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the trend of collecting unique, handcrafted furnishings and textiles, Well-Crafted seeks to showcase time-honored traditional techniques. Pair this color with charcoal, sage and linen whites for a color palette that helps to showcase these treasures.

name: RIVER BIRCH
description: River Birch is a nature-infused, lighter warm gray color with tones of green and yellow and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. With a stunning display of color variation in both its bark and leaves, River Birch is a perfect representation of this color. Create an earthy boho-inspired color palette by pairing River Birch with crisp whites, brushed brass and off-white linen.

name: CREEK BED
description: Creek Bed is a rich, midtone gray color with a green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. The plentiful display of nature through willows, grass, rocks and wildlife dotting the beds and banks of streams is the inspiration for this color. Pair Creek Bed with gray blue, grass green and cool gray for an indoor-outdoor color palette.

name: FISHING NET
description: Fishing Net is a lighter, mineral gray color with a touch of green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Outdoor recreational pursuits including fishing are the inspiration for this color. Complete your nautical theme by pairing Fishing Net with dark charcoal gray, marine blue and linen white.

name: HIGHLAND COUNTRY
description: Highland Country is a natural, heather midtone gray color with a touch of green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. The mountainous regions and elevated high hills are the inspiration behind Highland Country. Pair this color with ocean blue, olive green, black, muted peach and golden yellow for a Japandi-inspired color palette.

name: SAGE HEATHER
description: Sage Heather is a nature-inspired, midtone gray color with green undertones and part of our New Neutrals Collection. The wide array of wild and planned gardens each spring inspired this color. Sage Heather is a versatile, rich neutral color that works well for both interiors and exteriors. Paint this color on the exterior of your home for a nod to the indoor-outdoor lifestyle.

name: MISTY LAKE
description: Misty Lake is a cozy, foggy, lighter gray color with a touch of blue and part of our New Neutrals Collection. The morning mist coming off the lake in the early morning is inspiration for this color. Misty Lake is a lovely color addition to a lake or mountain cabin aesthetic. Or paint on the kitchen island or millwork for a touch of classic, muted neutral color.

name: FOGGY SEASCAPE
description: Foggy Seascape is a muted, lighter gray color with just a hint of green-blue undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Taking inspiration from the misty view off the ocean at dawn that is captured in many landscape paintings, Foggy Seascape creates a subtle note of casual elegance to any space. Pair with gray blue, muted coral and crisp white for a beachside cottage color palette.

name: REST EASY
description: Rest Easy is a lighter, mineral gray color with a note of green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Meditation rooms and spaces designed for relaxation continue to trend and provide the inspiration for this color. An easy neutral color that works with almost any design style, Rest Easy is a lovely color addition to bath and spa rooms to complete a restful retreat.

name: CLOUD COVER
description: Cloud Cover is a soft, light and airy greige color with a touch of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This neutral color plays well with both warm and cool colors and is an ideal choice for many design styles. Infuse Cloud Cover into a guest room to create a restful oasis.

name: THROWING SHADE
description: Throwing Shade is an easy-going, lighter shade of gray color with a touch of blue undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A fun play on the phrase, "throwing shade," this adaptable neutral color is an effortless color option for a variety of design styles. Pair with other cool neutrals, plus stone, darker woods and colored glass for an easy, casual-classic design aesthetic.

name: DISTANT DUSK
description: Distant Dusk is an understated, versatile gray color with a hint of brown and green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A sense of impending nightfall is the inspiration for this neutral color and is an elegant, classic gray that infers a sense of cozy charm. Paint on kitchen cabinetry and pair with cool stone counters, aged brass accents and dark hardwood floors for an effortlessly modern design aesthetic.

name: GARDEN WARBLER
description: Garden Warbler is a moody, warm greige color with a tinge of violet and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the trending hobby of birding, viewing the shy little birds in nature, the Garden Warbler is an enriching neutral color that harmonizes well with other colors. Paint the kitchen cabinetry Garden Warbler and accent the walls with a neutral white, then add stonework, aged bronze accents and warm woods to complete a transitional design aesthetic.

name: SHOU SUGI BAN
description: Shou Sugi Ban is a deep, cool, organic gray color with a true black undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the ancient Japanese architectural technique of preserving wood by charring it with fire, this dark neutral color displays the characteristics of a charred wood surface. Add a touch of drama to the exterior of your home by painting it Shou Sugi Ban and accenting with copper or bronze for a modern minimalist aesthetic.

name: DOLPHIN POD
description: Dolphin Pod is a calm, midtone warm gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by our social ocean friends, this neutral color creates depth and is an ideal choice for cabinets and trim work. Pair Dolphin Pod with misted blues and greens, highlight with cool white and accent with black for a luxury beachside aesthetic.

name: GREAT GRAY OWL
description: Great Gray Owl is a stately, enriching midtone warm gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the elusive, dapper, wise owl with its feathers a mix of silvery gray, fine white and brown streaks, this color is an ode to nature's beauty. Great Gray Owl is a neutral color with depth and works well on cabinetry and millwork.

name: CHATEAU GRAY
description: Chateau Gray is a lighter, vintage pewter shade of gray color with a touch of red and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the large country manors and wine regions of France, Chateau Gray takes us on a journey to relaxation. This stately neutral color is versatile and ideal for a variety of design styles.

name: BLOWIN' IN THE WIND
description: Blowin' In the Wind is a lighter, silvery shade of gray color with just a hint of yellow and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With a nod to music history, "Blowin' In the Wind," the famous Bob Dylan song from 1963, this neutral color moves with the light and is an ideal choice for a whole home color. Paint a living room with Blowin' In the Wind and set the space with an eclectic mix of furnishings and art for a modern aesthetic.

name: GRAY SOAPSTONE
description: Gray Soapstone is a stormy, lighter shade of gray color with a hint of blue and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the classic architectural stone that graces many homes, this neutral color resonates class and style and is an ideal color choice for a variety of design styles. Pair with deep navy and neutral white for a easy, go-to color palette.

name: MARENGO
description: Marengo is a cool, charcoal gray color with a touch of blue and black undertones and part of our New Neutrals Collection. In Spanish, Marengo means dark gray so is a fitting word for this shade of neutral gray color. With an air of mystery, Marengo is an ideal choice for spaces needing a touch of drama.

name: FLEUR DE SEL
description: Fleur de Sel color is a light, salty neutral gray inspired by the flower-like pattern of salt crystals that form on the seawater once it evaporates. This achromatic, neutral color is a versatile color ideal for most design styles. Pair with a warm gray, charcoal and crisp, cool white for a modern, industrial color palette.

name: NEUTRAL TERRITORY
description: Neutral Territory color is a versatile, lighter shade of grayish beige that perfectly balances warm and cool tones, making it an ideal neutral for a variety of design styles. Its subtle warmth adds a touch of coziness without being overpowering, offering a grounded and calming presence. Pair it with ocean blues, slate, or warmer grays to achieve a sophisticated, beachside cottage palette, or use it as a backdrop to complement bolder accents. Neutral Territory effortlessly brings harmony and balance to any room.

name: NEUTRAL WAVE
description: Neutral Wave is a lighter, achromatic shade of neutral gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the clean, neutral shade of this color, Neutral Wave is an ideal neutral color for a variety of design styles. Pair with shell pink, misty green and sand for a vintage-inspired color palette.

name: MIDDLE GRAY
description: Middle Gray is a midtone shade of neutral gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. As a neutral achromatic gray, Middle Gray is a versatile color for many design aesthetics. For an modern color palette, pair with other cool grays, black, navy and crisp white.

name: STONE GRAY
description: Stone Gray is a midtone shade of neutral gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. As an intermediate color between black and white, Stone Gray is an achromatic neutral and is the color of a cloud-covered sky, of ash and of lead. Well within the bounds of neutral gray, Stone Gray is an ideal color choice if you're looking for a modern industrial design color to get started. Pair with cool white and black, add a dose of metal and leather to complete the aesthetic.

name: DARK GRAY
description: Dark Gray is a darker shade of neutral gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. As an achromatic gray, this versatile neutral color creates depth and drama. For a Scandi-inspired color palette, pair Dark Gray with misty green gray, warm beige, olive and linen white.

name: CLOUD COMPUTING
description: Cloud Computing is a light and airy cool gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by technological advancements via the internet, this neutral color highlights the versatility of gray and is ideal for a variety of design styles. Pair with deep olive green and warm woods for an elegant, serene space.

name: HEATHER GRAY
description: Heather Gray is a midtone, feathery shade of gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Bordering on a true neutral gray, Heather Gray creates a cozy depth to space. For a monochromatic color palette, pair this color with black and crisp, cool white.

name: CARBON FIBER
description: Carbon Fiber is a deep, moody black color with a touch of blue undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. For an elegant, moody vibe, pair Carbon Fiber with lush velvets, warm woods and contemporary art for an homage to Manhattan's Upper East Side.

name: MUTED GRAY
description: Muted Gray is a classic, midtone gray color with a slight tinge of green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This soft, neutral color creates the perfect canvas for bolder décor and is a sophisticated neutral fit for more historic color palettes to help create a more dramatic statement. Pair with crisp whites, lighter grays, and teal for a classic, traditional color palette.

name: COLD EMBRACE
description: Cold Embrace is a stormy, cool toned, light gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. As a cooler gray color, Cold Embrace is an ideal choice for most design styles including beachside cottage and modern loft, and this neutral color will add a calming presence anywhere its used.

name: SILVER CHALICE
description: Silver Chalice is a silvery, cool, medium shade of gray color with a hint of blue and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With its relatively neutral undertones and soft, stormy presence, Silver Chalice is a beautiful, versatile color for a serene aesthetic. For a casual-chic, farmhouse look, pair Silver Chalice with neutral white and add black and white photography, wicker baskets and warm woods.

name: GRIS
description: Gris is a darker midtone shade of stormy, neutral gray color with a slight violet tone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. The French name for gray, Gris, inspires the name of this color and is a shade that creates an elegant aesthetic for interiors and exteriors. Create an inviting space by painting Gris in a dining room for a touch of refinement.

name: CONCRETE JUNGLE
description: Concrete Jungle is a saturated, midtone shade of gray color with a hint of pink undertone and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Cool and confident, Concrete Jungle is a neutral color that creates a polished look to any room. Create a welcoming entry by painting this color on your front door and finish the entry design with aged bronze lighting and slate planters.

name: ARTEMISIA
description: Artemisia is a silvery blue gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the array of aromatic ornamental herbs and shrubs that take on a range of hues including silver-gray, Artemisia is an ideal color to use as a transition between intense colors or to create contrast. This pleasant neutral color can create a refined look to a living or dining space.

name: DIGITAL NOMAD
description: Digital Nomad is a lighter blue gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. For those who travel the world in search of meaning and inspiration, this neutral cool gray is inspired by you. Digital Nomad creates a relaxed vibe and is a lovely choice for kitchen cabinetry and millwork.

name: METAVERSE
description: Metaverse is a lighter blue gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the technological advancements in digital experiences, this cool neutral color inspires modern, hip vibes and is a great choice for industrial color palettes. For those who lean more traditional, Metaverse is also a great choice for walls or cabinetry to create cozy, classic vibes.

name: KICK THE CAN
description: Kick the Can is a medium shade of neutral gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. As a neutral color, Kick the Can is incredibly versatile and is ideal in almost any interior or exterior space. Add depth to millwork by painting it with Kick the Can and pairing with a neutral white for a classic, refined space.

name: SLATE GRAY
description: Slate Gray is a midtone, mineral shade of blue gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. As a cooler toned neutral, Slate Gray is a modern shade that works wonderfully with almost every hue. For a modern color palette, pair Slate Gray with neutrals like beige or sand, then add a brighter color like orange.

name: WEATHERED GRAY
description: Weathered Gray is a lighter shade of misty cool gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With a touch of stormy blue and a hint of cloudy skies, Weathered Gray is a cooler neutral that invites a relaxed atmosphere. Pair with navy, crisp white and sage green for a classic beachside color palette.

name: MISTY SEASCAPE
description: Misty Seascape is a light, misty blue gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This nature-inspired, vaporous cool neutral color is a calm and welcoming hue. Pair Misty Seascape with cool white, warm sand and reedy green for a coastal cottage escape color palette.

name: GUSTAVIAN GRAY
description: Gustavian Gray is a lighter shade of cool gray with a touch of blue and green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the Swedish design style developed by Swedish king Gustav and is marked by grayed pastels, lots of whites and creams, painted furniture, clean simple lines, and fabulous lighting. Gustavian Gray is a chameleon-like color that changes depending on the light. Keeping in line with Swedish influences, pair Gustavian Gray with white, cream, pink and sky blue for a refined, yet rustic, color palette.

name: MARINESCAPE
description: Marinescape is a leaden sky shade of blue gray color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by views of distant seas and harbor scenes through an artistic lens, this cooler neutral is an inviting color choice for any space set for relaxation. Pair Marinescape with reedy greens, warm sand and delphinium violets and pinks for a Maine peninsula harbor-influenced color palette.

name: HELIOTROPE GRAY
description: Heliotrope Gray is a misty, silvery lighter shade of gray with a touch of lavender and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the perennial-like flower with cluster-like blooms in colors ranging from pinks to lavenders, Heliotrope Gray is an inviting, nostalgic-influenced color that is ideal for spaces of relaxation. Pair this cool neutral color with plum, magenta and warm beige for a historic Victorian-influenced color palette.

name: WINTERFELL
description: Winterfell is a lighter shade of cool gray and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the literal translation 'winter coat' but more recently by a well known show that depicted the capital of the north known as 'Winterfell.' By whichever influence that suits you, this cool neutral is versatile and ideal for a wide variety of design styles. Pair with warm beige, cool white, and navy for a classic, traditional color palette.

name: CHARRED
description: Charred is a deep, soft black color with a touch of blue and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the color of wood after a burn scar, the dark, neutral color creates a dramatic impact to any space. Paint Charred on your front door and shutters for a classic, refined exterior statement.

name: LET'S GET COZY
description: Let's Get Cozy is a soft, natural beige color with a hint of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by creating a calm and comfortable atmosphere, Let's Get Cozy is a versatile go-to beige for a wide variety of traditional and modern design styles. Consider Let's Get Cozy with other natural shades to create minimalist look or pair with dusty pastels for a vintage-inspired aesthetic.

name: WARM EMBRACE
description: Warm Embrace is a quiet beige color with a touch of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With a nod to a cozy hug and a touch of romance, Warm Embrace promotes a calm atmosphere and is an ideal choice for spaces needing quiet contemplation and reflection. Consider Warm Embrace for cottagecore and vintage-inspired spaces.

name: ANCIENT GRAIN
description: Ancient Grain is an epicurean brown color with a touch of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. An enveloping brown color inspired by its namesake, Ancient Grain is a grounding, soft brown perfect for reading nooks and bohemian-inspired spaces.

name: HOMESPUN CHARM
description: Homespun Charm is a light, quiet beige color with a touch of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by quaint country living and simpler times, Homespun Charm is a comfortable warm, versatile neutral suitable for use in a wide array of traditional and modern design styles. Beachside cottages and cozy cabins are ideal spaces for Homespun Charm.

name: BUTTERED CROISSANT
description: Buttered Croissant is a velvety light tan color with a touch of yellow undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the flaky, buttery morning treat, Buttered Croissant creates a calm atmosphere and is ideal as a whole home color or a quiet retreat.

name: BOOK BINDING
description: Book Binding is a midtone beige color with a touch of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the handcrafted art of binding books, this medium shade of brown creates a thoughtful, serene space and is an ideal color for dining and entertainment spaces to create an earthy backdrop.

name: FRENCH PRESS COFFEE
description: French Press Coffee color is a dense, deep brown color with a touch of red undertone. Lush and saturated, it contains rich notes of fresh roasted coffee beans and is a bold color choice fit for both entertaining and private spaces. For a dark acadamia aesthetic, pair French Press Coffee with other earthy, moody neutrals for a cozy, intimate atmosphere.

name: CLOUDS IN MY COFFEE
description: Clouds in My Coffee is a midtone beige color with a touch of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the famous lyrics in the song "You're So Vain" by Carly Simon, Clouds in My Coffee is a versatile warm neutral ideally suited for spaces seeking comfort and ease in design. Pair Clouds in My Coffee with rustic textures and pottery, rich woods, plants and iron work for a vintage-inspired aesthetic.

name: DOE EYED
description: Doe Eyed is a lush earthy warm neutral color with a touch of pink undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Sunbaked and grounded, Doe Eyed pairs well with other warm neutrals and whites. Create a cottagecore retreat by painting a space Doe Eyed, then accenting with antique brass elements and pastel textiles.

name: ORGANIC COFFEE
description: Organic Coffee is a rich, nature-inspired, dark brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With aromatic notes of autumn and fresh walnut, Organic Coffee is a sophisticated color choice ideal for spaces craving bold choices such as dining rooms and entryways. Organic Coffee is also a perfect color choice as an accent for a variety of exterior architectural design styles.

name: COLD BREW
description: Cold Brew is a dark coffee brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A full-bodied color with a touch of cinnamon-red undertone makes Cold Brew a perfect color choice for spaces craving a bit of drama. Create a striking backdrop in a bedroom by pairing Cold Brew with other brighter neutrals to set an elegant, cocoon-like, cozy space.

name: BROWNSTONE
description: Brownstone is a dark, sandstone brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Evoking a sense of historic architectural grandeur, Brownstone is an excellent color choice for both traditional and modern spaces. Reminiscent of its namesake, pair Brownstone with other warm neutrals and off-whites for a classic exterior color palette.

name: BISTRE PIGMENT
description: Bistre Pigment is a deep, blackened brown color with a touch of gray and violet and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Referencing the historic color of ink used by Old Masters painters for their drawings, Bistre Pigment is a striking, soot brown ideal for libraries and dens to create cozy vibes and is a perfect backdrop for modern and contemporary artwork.

name: CAFÉ NOIR
description: Café Noir is a sumptuous, deep brown color with a touch of violet and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This roasted, nutty brown color creates a moody, sophisticated vibe for dark academia and bohemian-inspired spaces. Café Noir is also a perfect color to accompany jewel tone hues and crisp whites for a modern, loft aesthetic fit for a collection of contemporary art.

name: ROSY TAUPE
description: Rosy Taupe is a midtone, warm taupe brown color with a touch of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This hot mocha spice color looks delightful when paired with soft shell pinks and warm whites for a vintage-inspired aesthetic. Rosy Taupe is also perfect for those spaces that call for a cozy, warm neutral.

name: TRIPLE CHOCOLATE MOUSSE
description: Triple Chocolate Mousse is a decadent, midtone brown color with a hint of red and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Rich and chocolatey, Triple Chocolate Mousse creates a velvety backdrop and is an ideal warm neutral color for spaces where you want to create a cozy, enveloping aesthetic such as reading nooks, dens and bedrooms.

name: LEATHER BOUND
description: Leather Bound is a meditative, midtone brown color with a hint of red. Thoughtful and restorative, this warm neutral color sets a contemplative mood as a backdrop hue for vintage-inspired décor and is a perfect choice for libraries filled with Leather Bound journals.

name: PORCINI MUSHROOM
description: Porcini Mushroom is a midtone, earthy, mushroom brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. The influence of nature is apparent in this grounding warm neutral color and is ideal in spaces where an indoor-outdoor lifestyle is key. Pair Porcini Mushroom with rustic woods and stone for classic, traditionally elegant design aesthetic.

name: CHICORY COFFEE
description: Chicory Coffee is a darkly roasted grounding brown color with a touch of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With its nutty, woodsy influences, Chicory Coffee is a warm neutral color that envelopes a space in dramatic warmth and is the perfect touch for a dazzling backdrop to classic, Traditional Italian and Spanish design styles.

name: DEEP TAUPE
description: Deep Taupe is a deep, stately brown color with a touch of gray and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Saturated and rich, Deep Taupe is a lovely backdrop color choice against brighter colors, warm woods and brass accents. Pair with blues, olives, gray and rust for a modern color palette.

name: WILD BUFFALO
description: Wild Buffalo is a deep, earthy brown color with a hint of red undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the majestic, wild beasts, Wild Buffalo is an ideal color choice for bohemian and ranch styles. Pair with other lighter warm neutrals, soft sage greens and a touch of muted blues for an indoor-outdoor color palette.

name: CASSEL EARTH
description: Cassel Earth is a deep, blackened brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Also known as Van Dyke brown or Cologne earth, this earthy, warm neutral color is inspired by the brown pigment around since the 17th-century and thought to have been used by Old Masters painters Rubens and Van Dyke. Bring out the artistic side in your space by pairing Cassel Earth with other warm neutrals, soft lavender and pink, and a muted yellow to create a color palette with Renaissance inspiration.

name: SAUTÉED CREMINI
description: Sautéed Cremini is a warm muted, classic taupe brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With its complexity of undertones edging on gray, green and brown, Sautéed Cremini is a versatile warm neutral color that underscores an elegant touch to any space and is a great color choice for entries, dining and living spaces.

name: WILD MAITAKE
description: Wild Maitake is a midtone warm taupe color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With a touch of gray and brown, this warm neutral color is a versatile choice ideal for almost any design style. Design with a comfortable influence of the hygge aesthetic by pairing Wild Maitake with weathered woods and reclaimed furnishings.

name: STONE GROUND
description: Stone Ground is an earthy, midtone warm taupe color and part of the New Neutrals Collection. With a touch of gray and green, Stone Ground is a versatile neutral color choice for a modern farmhouse design style. Or for an eye-catching look, pair this color with citrus for a fashionable, modern color palette.

name: DESERT NOMAD
description: Desert Nomad is a versatile, midtone warm taupe color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Globally-inspired, this dusty, well-traveled neutral color with a hint of gray and green creates an understated chic backdrop in desert boho design styles.

name: DUSTY COBBLESTONE
description: Dusty Cobblestone is a midtone, lush warm neutral color with a touch of gray and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. With an homage to heirloom quality, Dusty Cobblestone begs you to walk through vestiges of times past. Pair with marine blues and chocolate browns for a traditional cottage exterior color palette.

name: STONE COTTAGE
description: Stone Cottage is a grounded, midtone warm taupe color with a touch of gray and green and is part of our New Neutrals Collection. Provide a warm and welcoming invitation to house guests by pairing Stone Cottage with cream, sage and mauve to complete a cottagecore dream retreat. Paint on kitchen cabinetry and pair with white marble and antique brass for a touch of classic luxury.

name: GO QUIETLY
description: Go Quietly color is a soft, sun-aged warm off-white that exudes serenity and calm. This soothing hue creates a tranquil, inviting atmosphere, making it an ideal choice for bedrooms, meditation spaces, or wabi sabi-inspired designs. Its understated warmth effortlessly brings a sense of casual tranquility to any space.

name: ELUSIVE MOREL
description: Elusive Morel is a warm, midtone mushroom brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by mushroom hunting and locating these edible treats, pair this color with other nature-based hues like foliage greens and deeper woody browns for a moody, organic color palette.

name: ROAD LESS TRAVELED
description: Road Less Traveled is a rich and timeless midtone brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This versatile neutral color features a balance of warmth and coolness and works beautifully in both traditional and transitional spaces. Take the Road Less Traveled and paint this color on the walls and trim of a living space and pair with crisp white furnishings and lots of original artwork for a luxurious, cozy aesthetic.

name: RUGGED INDIVIDUAL
description: Rugged Individual is a rich and moody, midtone brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Create visual interest in a space by pairing this warm neutral color with dark woods for a casual, masculine aesthetic. Or paint on the walls and ceiling in an entry way and pair with red and yellow artwork and furnishings for a cheerful, unexpected atmosphere.

name: MEDIUM ROAST
description: Medium Roast is a classic, toasty midtone brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Notes of earthy warm coffee with slight sweetness add balance and harmony to this warm neutral color. To create your own coffeehouse aesthetic, pair Medium Roast with other warm neutrals and a spot of one or two more vibrant hues like leafy green and citrus orange to balance out the space.

name: THREE BEARS
description: Three Bears is a deep and dependable brown color with a hint of yellow and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the classic children's story, "Goldilocks and the Three Bears," create your own fairytale storybook cottage aesthetic by painting this warm neutral color in a living space and pair with vintage furnishings and grandma's textiles for a touch of homespun charm.

name: VINTAGE FINDS
description: Vintage Finds is a spice-infused, rich brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by Saturdays scouring flea markets for the perfect addition to a design project, Vintage Finds is a charming warm neutral color to add to a traditional cottage. Pair with heirloom textiles and furnishings to complete this eclectic space. For a warm, Scandinavian-inspired aesthetic, pair Vintage Finds with other lighter warm, tonal neutrals and spare furnishings.

name: CANOE CLUB
description: Canoe Club is a deep, rich nutty brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Playing up the inspiration of a retro university sports aesthetic, pair this dark brown neutral color with deep reds, blues and greens, along with a touch of charcoal for true dark academia vibes.

name: KICKIN' IT OLD SCHOOL
description: Kickin' It Old School is a dark, earthy rich brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Play up the fun of this slang term meaning "to hang out like we used to back in the day." With its versatility, this warm neutral color works in both casual, rustic and sleek, modern spaces.

name: RUGGEDLY HANDSOME
description: Ruggedly Handsome is a dark, homey brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With nature as a guide, pair with warm neutral color with soft greens, rust, charcoal and spring bud yellow for a rugged, cabin aesthetic. Or play up a dark academia vibe by pairing with black, moss and pine green, garnet, and muted gray.

name: ALPINE CHAMOISEE
description: Alpine Chamoisee is a bucolic, dark brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the color of the Alpine goats roaming the hills of France, this warm neutral color creates an earthy, cozy warmth, whether rustic or refined. Create a warm minimalist aesthetic by pairing with lighter warm beiges, olive green, mineral blue and golden yellow.

name: AFTERNOON TEA SERVICE
description: Afternoon Tea Service is a tea-stained, midtone brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the British tradition of afternoon tea, this warm neutral color is fitting for a classic, pastoral design aesthetic.

name: DISTILLERY
description: Distillery is an earthy, rustic dark brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. With influences of aged whisky barrels and handcrafted local flavors, Distillery is an optimal warm neutral color for traditional design styles. Pair with copper, brick, warm whites and a touch of red for a classic distillery aesthetic.

name: RAW CACAO BEAN
description: Raw Cacao Bean is a deep, rich organic brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the purest form of chocolate, this nutty warm neutral color is fitting for a space focused on indoor-outdoor living. Pair with grassy greens, teak wood and black ceramics for a zen-infused retreat.

name: HABERDASHERY
description: Haberdashery is a richly-pigmented, deep brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the old-fashioned word meaning a shop that sells men's fashion, accessories and notions, this traditional masculine-influenced warm neutral color is a fitting choice to pair with golden yellow, marine blue, and brick red, along with tweed and chintz fabrics, tufted furnishings, and natural woods for a classic British-vintage design aesthetic.

name: DOUBLE FUDGE
description: Double Fudge is a richly decadent, dense brown color with a touch of red and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Create a delectable backdrop using this deep brown color and highlight with shades of blue such as navy, turquoise or pale sky for a classic balance of warm and cool hues. Or pair with brick red, russet and warm white for an autumnal color palette.

name: COFFEE PURVEYORS
description: Coffee Purveyors is a warm, full-bodied dark brown color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by stores supplying small batch locally-produced coffees, this nutty, aromatic warm neutral color is a fitting choice for both modern and traditional spaces. Pair Coffee Purveyors with soft coral, sky blue, and golden yellow colors, along with rustic woods and charcoal drawings for a lake cabin aesthetic.

name: APPLE CINNAMON
description: Apple Cinnamon is a rich, toasty dark brown color with a touch of orange. Tasty and delicious, Apple Cinnamon is the perfect morning treat, as well as the inspiration for this warm neutral color. Pair with warm cream and chocolate, as well as stone, metal and wicker to complete a serene space.

name: TASTY TIRAMISU
description: Tasty Tiramisu is a lush, deep brown color with a slight hint of red and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This delectable dessert is the inspiration behind this dark warm neutral color and is a pleasing choice for both traditional and modern spaces. Create an earthy, boho-inspired color palette by partnering Tasty Tiramisu with forest green, gray blue, rust, obsidian and other warm neutrals.

name: ICED COFFEE
description: Iced Coffee is a cozy, midtone beige color with a touch of yellow and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Creamy and warm, Ice Coffee is the perfect midday pick-me-up and inspiration for this warm neutral color. Create an autumnal, sweater weather color palette by partnering Iced Coffee with deep, forest green, brownish-black, terracotta orange and muted gray.

name: QUINOA BOWL
description: Quinoa Bowl is an organic, midtone tan color with a touch of yellow and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the ancient grain that has been trending in health and wellness, Quinoa Bowl is a easy-going tan color that is versatile and can work in almost any space. Pair Quinoa Bowl with warm white, muted sky blue, muddy pink and chocolate for a meditative color palette.

name: CAMPSITE
description: Campsite is a midtone khaki tan color with a slight hint of gray and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Organic and nature-inspired, Campsite conjures memories of summers spent camping in the great outdoors. Bring this inspiration home by pairing this color with deep sage, warm white and terracotta orange for a rustic, outdoorsy color palette.

name: SUGAR SHACK
description: Sugar Shack is an earthy, deep bronze color with syrup tones and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Inspired by the sap houses primarily located in Canada and northern New England where tree sap is stored and boiled into maple syrup, this warm color is ideal for cozy, cabin vibes. Pair this rich color with crisp white and warm woods for a classic, traditional aesthetic.

name: ENTRY COAT RACK
description: Entry Coat Rack is an rustic, vintage-inspired deep shade of brown color with a touch of yellow and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Warm and welcoming, Entry Coat Rack invites guests to stay for awhile. Pair with cool blue gray, warm white and charcoal in the entry for a nod to classic Craftsman color palettes.

name: TO THE MANOR BROWN
description: To the Manor Brown is a classic and timeless dark shade of brown color with just a hint of yellow and part of our New Neutrals Collection. To the Manor Brown is a play on the phrase first coined by Shakespeare in 1603 in his play "Hamlet," act 1, scene 4: "But to my mind, though I am native here. And to the manner born, it is a custom. More honored in the breach than the observance." In modern times, it means born into a life of wealth and privilege. This versatile color is an ideal choice for cabinetry, millwork and exterior spaces.

name: OPEN SESAME
description: Open Sesame is an organic, midtone warm neutral color with a hint of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A magical phrase noted in the classic children's story, "Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves," in Antoine Galland's version of One Thousand and One Nights. It opens the mouth of a cave in which forty thieves have hidden a treasure. Create your own magic by pairing Open Sesame with soft coral, sage and sky blue for a desert modern color palette.

name: SKEIN OF YARN
description: Skein of Yarn is a warm, cozy light neutral color with a trace of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Knit a natural, wintry color palette from this neutral color by pairing Skein of Yarn with greige, cream and soft gray. To spice up the color palette, add brick and spicy hot chocolate and warm up by the fire.

name: STONE PEDESTAL
description: Stone Pedestal is a rich, creamy neutral color with a slight touch of green and yellow and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A classic, versatile neutral color that works well in any interior or exterior space, pair Stone Pedestal with charcoal, deep brown and warm white for a warm minimalist color palette.

name: PIGEONHOLE
description: Pigeonhole is a light, khaki greige color with just a hint of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Striking a nuanced balance between classic and modern, Pigeonhole is an ideal color choice for any design style. Pair with other warm neutrals, deep mauve, and mineral blues for a holistic, boho-chic color palette.

name: BASKET WEAVING
description: Basket Weaving is a grassy midtone, khaki greige color with just a hint of green and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Basket weaving or basketry is a very unique ancient craft, and traditionally, baskets were woven by hand from natural fibers, similar to the weaving of textiles. Add a touch of organic neutral coloring to your home by pairing Basket Weaving with spring greens and muted grays.

name: CATTAIL MARSH
description: Cattail Marsh is a midtone cool brown color with just a hint of mossy green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Vital to our ecosystem, a cattail marsh is a scenic wetland full of wildlife and vegetation where many visitors can enjoy learning about sealife, birding and hiking. Bring a touch of the outdoors home by pairing Cattail Marsh with grassy greens, muted gray blues and other warm neutrals.

name: OUTDOORSY
description: Outdoorsy is a smoky, deep shade of brown color with a touch of mossy green undertone and part of our New Neutrals Collection. This warm and homey brown is an ideal choice for rustic, indoor-outdoor design aesthetics. Consider using in a hall or entryway and pair with leather, woven grasses and antique bronze elements for an added welcoming touch.

name: ROAM WILD
description: Roam Wild is an alluring, outdoorsy deep brown color with a touch of green undertones and part of our New Neutrals Collection. Avid hikers love roaming the local trails and this love of the outdoors inspired the color Roam Wild. This warm neutral color works effortlessly with natural textures such as wood and stone. Build on this mood by pairing Roam Wild with grassy greens, marshy yellows, lighter warm neutrals and warm whites.

name: MOONSTONE BEACH
description: Moonstone Beach is a light, warm greige color and part of our New Neutrals Collection. A touch of gray gives this subtle, soft color a sense of balance and tranquility. Inspired by the beautiful, wild and rustic beach along the central coast of California, Moonstone Beach adds a sense of balance and calm to any design space and is the perfect choice for beach cottage design styles.
